\h 1 Shemuel
\toc1 1 Shemuel
\toc2 1 Shemuel
\toc3 1 She
\mt1 1 Shemuel
\is1 Introduction
\ip This document tells about the people of the nation of Yisrael (called вҖҳIsraelвҖҷ in older Bibles) at the time when Shemuel (commonly, but wrongly known as вҖҳSamuelвҖҷ) was still their teacher through to when Sha'ul (commonly, but wrongly known as вҖҳSaulвҖҷ) led them as their first king. It also reveals the reasons why Sha'ul lost his position as king and why God promised to replace him with David.
\ip Long ago before Yisrael had a king, the people regarded their god as their ruler, but eventually they came to the point of asking God to give them a king to lead them. Both the king and the people were subject to God's leading and expected to obey God's laws.
\ip The main theme of this document is showing how peace and prosperity came when the people obeyed God, and if not, it could lead to destruction. And then sometimes God used his people to apply his discipline to other people groups. It pays to note what's written in 2:30 that goes, вҖңI will honour those who honour me, but those who despise me will be side-lined.вҖқ
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 Shemuel as Yisrael's judge \ior 1:1вҖ“7:17\ior*
\io1 Sha'ul becomes king \ior 8:1вҖ“10:27\ior*
\io1 The first years of Sha'ul's reign \ior 11:1вҖ“15:35\ior*
\io1 David and Sha'ul \ior 16:1вҖ“30:31\ior*
\io1 The death of Sha'ul and his sons \ior 31:1-13\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Elkanah and family at Shiloh
\rem /s1 Elkanah and His Family; Samuel's birth and childhood; The Birth of Samuel; Samuel's Birth and Dedication; Elkanah and His Family at Shiloh
\p
\v 1 There was a manВҰ125380 named ElkanahВҰ125389 from RamatayimВҰ125384-ZofimВҰ125385 \add who lived\add* in the Efrayimite hill country. (He was an EfrayimiteвҖ”the son of YerohamВҰ125392, son of ElihuВҰ125395,\x + \xo 1:1 \xt 1 Chr. 6:27,34.\x* son of TohuВҰ125398, son of ZufВҰ125401.)
\v 2 He had two wivesВҰ125406: HannahВҰ125409 (who had no children) andВҰ125404 PeninnahВҰ125412 (who had \add several\add* children).
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲEvery year\add* he wouldВҰ125420 \add take his family\add* to ShilohВҰ125431 to \add вүҲoffer sacrificesВҰ125428\add* to commanderВҰ125430 Yahweh. EliВҰ125436 was Yahweh's priestВҰ125439 there, and his twoВҰ125433 sonsВҰ125434 HofniВҰ125437 and PinehasВҰ125438 \add also served there\add*.
\p
\v 4 on the dayВҰ125443 that ElkanahВҰ125445 made his sacrificeВҰ125444, he would give portionsВҰ125453 \add of the cooked meat\add* to PeninnahВҰ125447 and to all her sons and daughtersВҰ125452,
\v 5 \add вүҲbutВҰ125455\add* he'd give a doubleВҰ125459 portionВҰ125457 to HannahВҰ125463 because he lovedВҰ125464 \add *her\add*, \add even though\add* YahwehВҰ125465 had \add вүҲnot enabled her to have children\add*.
\v 6 ThenВҰ125469 her rivalВҰ125470 would provokeВҰ125469 her andВҰ125469 \add вүҲtry to make her angry\add*, because YahwehВҰ125479 hadn't \add вүҲgiven her children\add*.
\v 7 And so it \add вүҲhappened every year\add*. Every time they went to Yahweh's \add вүҲtent\add*, \add @Peninnah\add* ridiculed him, and \add @Hannah\add* would weep and wouldn't eat.
\v 8 ThenВҰ125497 ElkanahВҰ125499 would \add вүҲask\add* her, вҖңHannahВҰ125501, why are you crying? And why aren'tВҰ125505 you eatingВҰ125506? And why \add вүҲare you so upset\add*? Isn't it better \add вүҲhaving me\add* than \add вүҲhaving\add* tenВҰ125514 sonsВҰ125515?вҖқ
\s1 Hannah and Eli
\rem /s1 Hannah and Eli; Hannah's Prayer for a Son
\p
\v 9 \add One time\add* HannahВҰ125518 got up after eating andВҰ125517 drinking at ShilohВҰ125521. (EliВҰ125524 the priestВҰ125525 was sittingВҰ125526 on the seatВҰ125529 near the entrance of Yahweh's \add вүҲtent\add*.)
\v 10 \add @Hannah\add* \add вүҲwas very upset\add*, and she prayedВҰ125539 to YahwehВҰ125542 and wept uncontrollably.
\v 11 ThenВҰ125546 she made a vow, saying, вҖңCommander YahwehВҰ125549, if you \add вүҲwould only notice the misery\add* of your female servant and rememberВҰ125558 me. Don't \add вүҲignore\add* \add *me\add*. \add вүҲHelp\add* your female servant \add вүҲto give birth to a son\add*, thenВҰ125546 I'llВҰ125569 give him to \add *you\add* \add вүҲfor his entireВҰ125571\add* lifeВҰ125574, and \add вүҲhe'll never have his hair cut\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 1:11: \xt Num 6:5.\x*
\p
\v 12 As sheВҰ125585 continued praying to YahwehВҰ125588, EliВҰ125589 was watchingВҰ125590 her mouthВҰ125593.
\v 13 \add вүҲNow\add* Hannah was \add вүҲpraying from her heartВҰ125600\add*, andВҰ125595 her lipsВҰ125602 were moving \add вүҲbutВҰ125595 she wasn't speakingВҰ125597 aloud\add*. EliВҰ125608 thought \add she must be\add* drunkВҰ125609,
\v 14 andВҰ125611 \add вүҲscolded\add* her, вҖңYou shouldn't be getting drunkВҰ125617. Get rid of yourВҰ125621 wine.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖңNo, my masterВҰ125628,вҖқ HannahВҰ125625 repliedВҰ125624, вҖңI'm a womanВҰ125629 \add вүҲwho's suffering deep down\add*. I haven't drunkВҰ125637 any wine or intoxicating drinkВҰ125635, \add вүҲbutВҰ125624 rather\add* I'veВҰ125637 been \add вүҲsharing my inner issues\add* with YahwehВҰ125628.
\v 16 Don't think that yourВҰ125650 female servantВҰ125650 is \add just\add* a worthlessВҰ125654 woman, because just now I was \add вүҲpraying as a result of my terrible anguishВҰ125658 andВҰ125659 frustration\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖң\add ThenВҰ125665\add* goВҰ125668 in peaceВҰ125669,вҖқ EliВҰ125666 replied. вҖңAnd may Yisrael'sВҰ125671 godВҰ125670 grantВҰ125672 yourВҰ125675 request thatВҰ125676 youВҰ125677 \add вүҲpresented to\add* himВҰ125678.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 вҖң\add вүҲPlease assume the best of\add* your female servantВҰ125682,вҖқ saidВҰ125680 \add @Hannah\add*, thenВҰ125680 sheВҰ125681 wentВҰ125685 onВҰ125684 her wayВҰ125687 and \add вүҲhad something to eat\add*, and \add вүҲsomething had changed inВҰ125684 her demeanor\add*.
\s1 Shemu'el's birth and dedication
\rem /s1 Samuel's Birth and Dedication
\p
\v 19 They \add all\add* gut up earlyВҰ125697 the \add next\add* morningВҰ125698 and worshippedВҰ125699 Yahweh \add again\add*, thenВҰ125697 theyВҰ125703 returnedВҰ125702 to theirВҰ125706 home atВҰ125698 RamahВҰ125707. ThenВҰ125697 ElkanahВҰ125709 \add вүҲslept withВҰ125698\add* his wife HannahВҰ125712, and Yahweh \add вүҲanswered herВҰ125714 prayer\add*.
\v 20 \add @Hannah\add* got pregnantВҰ125720, andВҰ125717 in due course, she gaveВҰ125722 birthВҰ125722 to a son. She named him вҖҳShemu'elвҖҷ \add (meaning вҖҳheard by GodвҖҷ, usually changed to вҖҳSamuelВҰ125728вҖҷ in English)\add* because she had requested him from YahwehВҰ125730.
\rem /s1 Hannah Dedicates Samuel
\p
\v 21 \add At the usual timeВҰ125744,\add* ElkanahВҰ125735 and all his householdВҰ125738 went \add to Shiloh\add* to \add вүҲofferВҰ125739 their sacrificesВҰ125743 and fulfill their vows\add* to YahwehВҰ125740.
\v 22 \add вүҲButВҰ125749\add* Hannah \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ125750 accompany them\add* because she'd told her husband, вҖңI'llВҰ125759 \add come and\add* bringВҰ125759 him when he's weanedВҰ125757. ThenВҰ125749 he can be \add вүҲtaken in to\add* YahwehВҰ125764 and \add вүҲpermanently\add* remainВҰ125765 thereВҰ125766.вҖқ
\v 23 вҖңDo \add вүҲwhat you think's best\add*,вҖқ her husbandВҰ125774 \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңStay until you've weaned him. May YahwehВҰ125785 \add вүҲdo whatever he saidВҰ125771\add* \add to you\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ125771\add* \add *she\add* stayed \add behind\add* andВҰ125771 breastfed her son until she \add вүҲeventually\add* weaned him.
\p
\v 24 \add The next year,\add* after she'd weanedВҰ125803 him, she tookВҰ125800 the youngВҰ125804 boy with \add #them\add*, along with threeВҰ125805 bullsВҰ125804, a \add вүҲsack\add* of flourВҰ125808, andВҰ125800 a \add вүҲcontainer\add* of wine. ThenВҰ125800 she broughtВҰ125811 him to Yahweh's \add вүҲtent\add* inВҰ125804 ShilohВҰ125815,
\v 25 andВҰ125823 after slaughteringВҰ125819 the bullВҰ125822, they took the boyВҰ125826 in to EliВҰ125829.
\v 26 вҖңPlease, my master,вҖқ \add @Hannah\add* said. вҖңAs your spirit lives, my master, I'm the womanВҰ125838 who was standing withВҰ125841 you here to pray to YahwehВҰ125833.
\v 27 I prayedВҰ125851 \add вүҲthatВҰ125858 YahwehВҰ125853 would give me a son, and he did, and this is him\add*.
\v 28 Also, I dedicated himВҰ125864 to Yahweh all his life, so he's now given to Yahweh.вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ125862 \add #they\add* worshippedВҰ125874 Yahweh thereВҰ125875.
\c 2
\s1 Hannah's praise
\rem /s1 Hannah's Prayer; Hannah's Prayer of Praise
\q1
\v 1 Then HannahВҰ125880 prayedВҰ125879, saying,\x + \xo 2:1-10: \xt Luk 1:46-55.\x*
\q1 вҖң\add вүҲI'm so happy withВҰ125884\add* Yahweh.
\q1 My strength comes from Yahweh.
\q1 I can \add вүҲloudly refute\add* my enemiesВҰ125892.
\q1 Because I'm \add вүҲso pleased that you rescued me\add*.
\b
\q1
\v 2 No one \add else\add* is holy like YahwehВҰ125900.
\q1 вүҲThere'sВҰ125897 certainly no one else who's like youВҰ125903.
\q1 No one else \add is like a\add* rockВҰ125905 \add to me\add* like ourВҰ125906 godВҰ125906 is.
\q1
\v 3 You all shouldn'tВҰ125908 speakВҰ125911 so proudly.
\q1 вүҲ\add вүЎDon't\add* let arroganceВҰ125915 come out of yourВҰ125916 mouthsВҰ125916.
\q1 Because YahwehВҰ125920 is a godВҰ125918 of knowledgeВҰ125919,
\q2 andВҰ125921 all actions are weighed by him.
\b
\q1
\v 4 Warriors have their bows shatteredВҰ125928,
\q1 butВҰ125929 thoseВҰ125929 who stumbledВҰ125929 \add вүҲare given extra\add* strengthВҰ125931.
\q1
\v 5 Those who had been satisfied \add now\add* hire themselvesВҰ125935 out for food,
\q2 but the hungryВҰ125936 people \add вүҲno longer lack\add*.
\q1 The woman who'd been childlessВҰ125942, gives birth to sevenВҰ125942,
\q2 but the woman withВҰ125934 many sonsВҰ125944 \add вүҲis depressed\add*.
\q1
\v 6 YahwehВҰ125947 puts to death and heВҰ125950 makesВҰ125949 aliveВҰ125949.
\q1 вүҲHeВҰ125951 sends down to the grave and bringsВҰ125950 up.
\q1
\v 7 YahwehВҰ125954 makes poor and makes rich.
\q1 вүҲHe humbles, and he also honours.
\q1
\v 8 He lifts the poor up from the dust,
\q1 вүҲand lifts up the needyВҰ125967 from the ash heap
\q1 so they can sitВҰ125968 with influential \add people\add*
\q1 вүҲand be given the seatВҰ125972 of honourВҰ125973.
\q1 The earth'sВҰ125978 foundations belong to YahwehВҰ125976вҖ”
\q1 he was the one who placed the worldВҰ125981 on top of them.
\q1
\v 9 He \add вүҲwatches over\add* those who are loyal to him,
\q1 butВҰ125987 wickedВҰ125987 \add people\add* will die inВҰ125988 the darknessВҰ125988,
\q2 because \add вүҲwe\add* don'tВҰ125992 succeed through our own strengthВҰ125993.
\q1
\v 10 It's Yahweh who shattersВҰ125999 our enemies.
\q1 He thundersВҰ126005 againstВҰ126002 \add #them\add* from the heavensВҰ126004.
\q1 Yahweh will judgeВҰ126007 the \add вүҲentire\add* earthВҰ126010,
\q1 and will give strengthВҰ126013 to the kingВҰ126014,
\q1 and will \add вүҲgive victory\add* to his chosen one.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Eli's Wicked Sons
\p
\v 11 Then ElkanahВҰ126021 \add and his family\add* returned to \add #their\add* homeВҰ126025 in RamahВҰ126022, butВҰ126020 young Shemuel \add stayed to\add* help EliВҰ126035 the priestВҰ126036 serve YahwehВҰ126031.
\s1 Eli's greedy sons
\rem /s1 The Sons of Eli; Eli's Wicked Sons
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲNow\add* Eli'sВҰ126039 sons were \add вүҲworthlessВҰ126041 scoundrels\add* who didn'tВҰ126042 obey YahwehВҰ126046.
\v 13 It was the customВҰ126048 of those priestsВҰ126049 that when anyone was offering a sacrificeВҰ126056 andВҰ126048 as soon as the meat was boilingВҰ126061, the priest's servantВҰ126059 would comeВҰ126058 along holding a three-pronged fork
\v 14 andВҰ126069 stick it into the pot or pan. The priestВҰ126082 would thenВҰ126069 \add вүҲclaim\add* whatever the fork broughtВҰ126079 up. That's what they did to all the Israelis who came to ShilohВҰ126091 \add to offer sacrifices\add*.
\v 15 Also, beforeВҰ126094 the fat \add was removed to\add* burn, the priest's servantВҰ126101 would say to the personВҰ126104 sacrificingВҰ126105, вҖңGive some meat to the priestвҖ”he doesn't want just boiledВҰ126115 meat \add all the time\add*вҖ”he'll take some raw meat \add as well\add* to roastВҰ126108.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 ButВҰ126121 if the person tried to say, вҖңOnce the fat has all been burnt, then take whatever you want for yourselfВҰ126130,вҖқ then he'd \add вүҲassert\add*, вҖңNo, you'd better giveВҰ126140 it \add right\add* now or I'll take it by forceВҰ126145.вҖқ
\v 17 And \add so\add* the actions of those youngВҰ126149 men were very wicked in Yahweh's mind because they \add just\add* treatedВҰ126157 sacrifices to Yahweh with contemptВҰ126157.
\s1 Young Shemuel starts serving at Shiloh
\rem /s1 The Child Samuel at Shiloh; Samuel at Shiloh
\p
\v 18 \add вүҲBy now\add* Shemuel was servingВҰ126164 YahwehВҰ126168, dressed in a priestly uniform made from linenВҰ126172.
\v 19 \add вүҲEachВҰ126190 year\add* his motherВҰ126179 would make a smallВҰ126175 robeВҰ126174 for him andВҰ126174 bring it when she came withВҰ126185 her husbandВҰ126188 to offerВҰ126189 \add #their sacrificesВҰ126192\add*.
\v 20 EliВҰ126196 would blessВҰ126195 ElkanahВҰ126199 and his wife and say, вҖңMay Yahweh \add вүҲgive more children for you through\add* this womanВҰ126210 in placeВҰ126212 of the \add boy\add* \add вүҲdedicated\add* to Yahweh.вҖқ ThenВҰ126195 they'd return homeВҰ126218.
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲSo\add* Yahweh visitedВҰ126222 HannahВҰ126226 and she went on to give birthВҰ126228 to threeВҰ126229 \add other\add* sonsВҰ126231 and twoВҰ126232 daughtersВҰ126233. \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* \add вүҲyoung\add* ShemuelВҰ126236 \add вүҲgrew up serving\add* Yahweh.
\s1 Eli and his children
\rem /s1 Eli and His Sons; Prophecy against Eli's Household
\p
\v 22 \add вүҲNow\add* EliВҰ126242 was very old and he had heardВҰ126245 all about what his sonsВҰ126251 were doingВҰ126250 to the Israeli people, and \add also\add* that they were sleeping around with the womenВҰ126261 who worked at the sacredВҰ126264 tentВҰ126264 entrance.
\v 23 вҖңWhy are you \add two\add* doingВҰ126270 all these things that I keep hearingВҰ126275 aboutвҖ”these evil things \add вүҲaffecting\add* all those peopleВҰ126283?вҖқ he \add вүҲasked\add* them.
\v 24 вҖңNo, my sonsВҰ126287. The reportsВҰ126292 thatВҰ126293 I keep hearingВҰ126295 Yahweh's peopleВҰ126297 passing on aren'tВҰ126289 goodВҰ126291!
\v 25 If someone sins against a person, then GodВҰ126307 will mediateВҰ126306 for him, butВҰ126306 if someone sins against Yahweh, who will \add вүҲspeak up\add* for that person?вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ126306\add* they wouldn't listenВҰ126318 to theirВҰ126320 father'sВҰ126320 advice because Yahweh wanted to put them to deathВҰ126325.
\p
\v 26 \add вүҲMeanwhile\add* the boyВҰ126327 Shemuel was growingВҰ126330 \add up\add*, and his goodВҰ126331 \add behaviour pleased\add* both YahwehВҰ126335 and \add вүҲthe peopleВҰ126339\add*.\x + \xo 2:26: \xt Luk 2:52.\x*
\s1 The prophecy against Eli's family
\rem /s1 The Prophecy against Eli's Family; A Warning for Eli's Family; Prophecy Against the House of Eli
\p
\v 27 \add вүҲOne day\add* one of God's \add prophets\add* cameВҰ126342 to EliВҰ126348 and told him, вҖңThis is what YahwehВҰ126353 saysВҰ126352, вҖҳDid\add n't\add* I clearly reveal myselfВҰ126355 to your ancestors when they were Far'oh's \add вүҲslaves\add* inВҰ126361 EgyptВҰ126361?
\v 28 And out of all the IsraeliВҰ126369 tribesВҰ126369, I choseВҰ126365 \add @your ancestor\add* to be a priestВҰ126372 to me, to goВҰ126373 up on myВҰ126381 altarВҰ126376, to burnВҰ126377 incenseВҰ126378, \add andВҰ126382\add* to \add вүҲwear the sacred apron in front of me\add*. Plus I gaveВҰ126382 your ancestors \add the rights to\add* all the burnt offeringsВҰ126389 made by the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ126370\add*.\x + \xo 2:28: a \xt Exo 28:1-4; \xo b \xt Lev 7:35-36.\x*
\v 29 Why do you \add вүҲdisrespect\add* sacrificesВҰ126395 and offerings thatВҰ126397 I commandedВҰ126398 \add the people\add* to bring to me \add вүҲatВҰ126395 my residence\add*. And \add вүЎwhy do\add* you honourВҰ126400 your sons more than me by fattening yourselvesВҰ126405 from the best of everyВҰ126407 offering of my people YisraelВҰ126410?вҖҷ
\p
\v 30 вҖңTherefore, this is what YahwehВҰ126416 the godВҰ126417 of YisraelВҰ126418 declares: вҖҳI indeedВҰ126419 said \add вүҲyour ancestors and then your descendants\add* would \add вүҲserve me forever\add*.вҖҷ ButВҰ126422 now \add вүҲI declare this\add* \add instead\add*: вҖҳ\add вүҲThis cannot continue\add* because I will honour those who honour me, butВҰ126422 those who despiseВҰ126439 me will be \add вүҲside-lined\add*.
\v 31 ListenВҰ126445, the timeВҰ126443 is comingВҰ126444 when I'llВҰ126453 \add вүҲbring you and your relatives to an endвҖ”none of your men will die of old age\add*
\v 32 andВҰ126468 you'll seeВҰ126458 distressВҰ126459 in my residence. I'llВҰ126465 do goodВҰ126464 for \add the rest of\add* YisraelВҰ126467, butВҰ126458 there'll never be another old manВҰ126471 in yourВҰ126472 home.
\v 33 I won'tВҰ126478 \add вүҲfinish\add* them off near my altarВҰ126483. Your eyesВҰ126487 will fail andВҰ126477 you'll grieveВҰ126488 \add вүҲinside\add*, butВҰ126477 your \add adult sons\add* will dieВҰ126496.
\v 34 This will be the signВҰ126502: it'll \add вүҲturn out\add* thatВҰ126503 yourВҰ126508 twoВҰ126507 sonsВҰ126508 HofniВҰ126511 andВҰ126512 Finehas will bothВҰ126507 dieВҰ126515 on the same dayВҰ126513.\x + \xo 2:34: \xt 1Sam 4:11.\x*
\v 35 ThenВҰ126518 I'll \add вүҲselect\add* another man to be a faithful priestВҰ126520 to meвҖ”he'll \add вүҲfollow my desires and do what's inВҰ126523 my mindВҰ126523\add*. I'll make \add вүҲhim and his faithful descendants to continue and to always serve me\add*.
\v 36 Any of yourВҰ126543 descendants who remainВҰ126542 \add вүҲalive\add* will have to go to him to request food and money and \add вүҲbeg\add* for some priestlyВҰ126558 work to earn \add вүҲsomething to eatВҰ126559\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\c 3
\s1 Yahweh calls Shemuel
\rem /s1 The Lord Appears to Samuel; Samuel's Calling and Prophetic Activity; The Lord Speaks to Samuel; The Lord Calls Samuel
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲMeanwhile young\add* Shemuel was servingВҰ126567 Yahweh \add вүҲunder\add* EliВҰ126572. In thoseВҰ126579 daysВҰ126578, Yahweh rarely \add вүҲspoke to the people or sent visionsВҰ126581\add*.
\p
\v 2 \add вүҲBy that time,\add* Eli'sВҰ126588 \add вүҲsight was very poor\add*вҖ”he could barely seeВҰ126598. \add One night when\add* he was sleeping in his place,\f + \fr 3:2 \ft Some translations use вҖҳroomвҖҷ here instead of вҖҳplaceвҖҷ, but it could easily be that he had a small bed in a corner somewhere.\f*
\v 3 andВҰ126604 ShemuelВҰ126604 was lyingВҰ126605 down in Yahweh's tent (whereВҰ126608 the boxВҰ126611 was that contained the \add вүҲstone slabs\add*), \add вүҲbutВҰ126600\add* God's lamp was still burning.
\v 4 YahwehВҰ126616 called out to ShemuelВҰ126619, and he \add вүҲcalled back\add*, вҖңI'm here. \add Coming.\add*вҖқ
\v 5 ThenВҰ126623 he ranВҰ126623 to EliВҰ126626 and said, вҖңHere I am, because you called me.вҖқ
\p вҖңI didn'tВҰ126634 call,вҖқ he said. вҖңGo back \add and\add* lie down.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ126623\add* he wentВҰ126639 \add back\add* and laid down.
\p
\v 6 YahwehВҰ126644 called againВҰ126646, вҖңShemuelВҰ126647.вҖқ
\p Shemuel got up and wentВҰ126650 to EliВҰ126653 and said, вҖңHere I am, because you called me.вҖқ
\p вҖңI didn'tВҰ126660 call, my son,вҖқ he said, вҖңGo back \add and\add* lie down.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 (\add At this point\add*, Shemuel didn'tВҰ126668 \add really\add* know Yahweh, because Yahweh hadn't revealedВҰ126674 \add himself\add* to him before.)
\v 8 Then Yahweh called Shemuel a thirdВҰ126685 timeВҰ126685. He got up and wentВҰ126687 to EliВҰ126690 and saidВҰ126691, вҖңHere I am, because you called me.вҖқ
\p Then Eli realised that it was Yahweh who was calling the boyВҰ126701
\v 9 and he told Shemuel, вҖңGo \add and\add* lie down. ThenВҰ126703 if he calls to you \add again\add*, \add вүҲjust answer\add*, вҖҳSpeak, YahwehВҰ126715, because your servantВҰ126718 is listeningВҰ126717.вҖҷ вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ126703\add* Shemuel wentВҰ126719 and laid down \add again\add* inВҰ126722 his placeВҰ126722.
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ126724 YahwehВҰ126725 cameВҰ126724 and \add вүҲstoodВҰ126726 nearby\add* and calledВҰ126727 \add вүҲlike he'd done the other\add* timesВҰ126730, вҖңShemuel, Shemuel.вҖқ
\p вҖңSpeak,вҖқ ShemuelВҰ126731 saidВҰ126734, вҖңbecause yourВҰ126739 servantВҰ126739 is listeningВҰ126738.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖңListen,вҖқ YahwehВҰ126743 told \add *him\add*, вҖңI'm aboutВҰ126749 to do something inВҰ126751 YisraelВҰ126751 thatВҰ126752 \add вүҲwill make everyone'sВҰ126753 ears tingleВҰ126756 when they hear it\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲWhen it happens\add*, I'llВҰ126762 \add вүҲdo everything that I'veВҰ126770 said about EliВҰ126765 andВҰ126775 his family\add*, from the beginningВҰ126774 to the endВҰ126775.
\v 13 I've told him \add already\add* that I'm about to \add вүҲeternally\add* judgeВҰ126781 his \add вүҲhouseholdВҰ126785\add* because \add вүҲhe knewВҰ126792 about the evil that was being done\add*, because his sonsВҰ126797 were \add вүҲbringingВҰ126795 cursesВҰ126795 onВҰ126789\add* themselves andВҰ126777 he didn'tВҰ126798 scold them.
\v 14 That's why I've promised Eli'sВҰ126805 \add вүҲfamily\add* that \add *their\add* disobedience can \add вүҲnever\add* be forgiven by means of sacrificesВҰ126813 or offeringsВҰ126814.
\s1 Shemuel tells Eli what Yahweh said
