\p \add At that time,\add* Yisrael went to war against the Philistines. They camped at Eben-Ezer and the Philistines camped at AfekВҰ126967.
\v 2 ThenВҰ126969 the Philistines lined up to meet Yisrael and the battle spreadВҰ126973. Yisrael was defeatedВҰ126975 by the Philistines and they killedВҰ126979 aboutВҰ126982 4,000 warriors in the battle line in the countrysideВҰ126981.
\v 3 \add вүҲAs\add* the people\f + \fr 4:3 \ft It seems that most translations assume that this is referring to the remainder of the warriors staggering back into the camp (which is certainly a possibility), but we've interpreted it as the people coming together (with their elders as it says), to try to figure out why they were defeated. (Similarly for v4.)\f* cameВҰ126986 into the camp, the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ126992\add* elders \add вүҲasked\add* \add themselves\add*, вҖңWhy did Yahweh \add вүҲallow the PhilistinesВҰ126999 to slaughter\add* us today? Let's get the boxВҰ127005 from ShilohВҰ127002 that contains \add the stone slabs with\add* Yahweh's agreement \add onВҰ127009 them\add*. \add вүҲOnce it's amongst us\add*, \add surely\add* it'll saveВҰ127010 us from \add вүҲdefeatВҰ126995 by\add* ourВҰ127012 enemiesВҰ127012.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ127014\add* the peopleВҰ127015 sentВҰ127014 \add <men\add* to ShilohВҰ127016 and from there theyВҰ127017 lifted the box containing Yahweh's agreement \add and the sacred platform\add* with the winged creatures.\f + \fr 4:4 \ft And with Commander Yahweh sitting on, above, or between them.\f* Eli'sВҰ127031 twoВҰ127028 sonsВҰ127029, HofniВҰ127037 and Finehas, were there with the box containing God's agreement.\x + \xo 4:4: \xt Exo 25:22.\x*
\p
\v 5 \add вүҲAs\add* the boxВҰ127042 with Yahweh's agreement \add вүҲwas carried\add* into the campВҰ127048, all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ127050\add* shoutedВҰ127053 so loud that the ground shookВҰ127055.
\v 6 WhenВҰ127058 the PhilistinesВҰ127059 heardВҰ127058 the \add вүҲnoise\add*, they saidВҰ127064, вҖңWhat's that loud shout inВҰ127070 the Hebrews' camp?вҖқ ThenВҰ127058 they realised that the boxВҰ127074 \add вүҲwithВҰ127070 Yahweh's covenant\add* had comeВҰ127076 into their camp
\v 7 andВҰ127081 they were afraid saying, вҖңA godВҰ127086 has comeВҰ127085 into the \add Israeli\add* campВҰ127089.вҖқ ThenВҰ127081 they said, вҖң\add вүҲThis means trouble\add*, because it wasn't like this yesterdayВҰ127097 \add вүҲor the previous daysВҰ127098\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲOh dear\add*! Who will rescue us from these mightyВҰ127106 gods? Those are the gods who struckВҰ127111 the Egyptians withВҰ127118 every plagueВҰ127117 inВҰ127118 the wildernessВҰ127118.
\v 9 Now we PhilistinesВҰ127123 \add вүҲreally need to fight with passion\add*, because if we don't, we'll ending up serving the HebrewsВҰ127126 just like they've had to serveВҰ127125 us. \add вүҲNow, gather your courage and fight for your lives\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ127134\add* the PhilistinesВҰ127135 foughtВҰ127134 \add hard\add*, and Yisrael was \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ127136\add*. \add вүҲMany warriors fled back to their tentsВҰ127140\add* and itВҰ127141 was a \add вүҲterrible\add* slaughterВҰ127142вҖ”30,000 footВҰ127149 soldiersВҰ127149 from Yisrael were killed.
\v 11 \add вүҲAs well as that,\add* the boxВҰ127151 with God's \add agreement\add* was takenВҰ127153, and Eli'sВҰ127157 twoВҰ127154 sonsВҰ127155 HofniВҰ127159 and Finehas were killed.
\s1 The death of Eli
\rem /s1 Death of Eli; The Death of Eli
\p
\v 12 A Benyamite manВҰ127163 ranВҰ127162 from the battleВҰ127166 line back to ShilohВҰ127168 that dayВҰ127169. His clothesВҰ127171 were torn andВҰ127162 \add вүҲhe was covered in dirt\add*.
\v 13 \add вүҲWhenВҰ127178\add* he arrivedВҰ127178 \add there\add*, EliВҰ127180 was sittingВҰ127181 onВҰ127200 a roadside seat watchingВҰ127188, because he was \add вүҲvery concerned\add* about the \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ127195\add*. AsВҰ127196 the man entered the city withВҰ127200 the news, all the \add вүҲpeople\add* started \add вүҲwailing loudly\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲAs\add* Eli heard the wailing, he \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖң\add вүҲWhat's that big commotionВҰ127215\add*?вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ127206\add* the manВҰ127217 ran over to Eli to \add вүҲtell him the news\add*.
\v 15 \add вүҲAt that time\add*, Eli was ninety-eight years old, andВҰ127223 he \add вүҲstared straight ahead\add* because he couldn't seeВҰ127233.
\v 16 The manВҰ127236 told \add *him\add*, вҖңI'm the one who's \add just\add* comeВҰ127241 from the battle line. I \add had to\add* fled from the battle line today.вҖқ
\p вҖңWhat was the issue, my son?вҖқ \add @Eli\add* \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p
\v 17 вҖңYisraelВҰ127262 fled \add вүҲdefeated\add* from the PhilistinesВҰ127264,вҖқ saidВҰ127260 the messengerВҰ127259. вҖңAnd also, there has been a terrible slaughterВҰ127266 of our peopleВҰ127269. \add вүҲWhat's more\add*, yourВҰ127273 twoВҰ127272 sonsВҰ127273, HofniВҰ127275 and Finehas, \add вүҲwere killed\add*, and the \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ127277 has been captured\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 \add вүҲThe moment\add* he mentionedВҰ127283 the capturing of God's boxВҰ127287, \add @Eli\add* fell backwardsВҰ127293 off the seatВҰ127292 beside the city gateВҰ127297. Because he was old and \add very\add* heavyВҰ127305, his neck brokeВҰ127298 and he diedВҰ127300. Eli had \add вүҲled\add* YisraelВҰ127310 for fortyВҰ127311 years.
\s1 The death of Finehas' widow
