\p
\v 19 \add вүҲNow\add* Finehas' wife (\add @Eli's\add* daughter-in-law) was pregnantВҰ127318вҖ”about to give birthвҖ”\add вүҲwhen\add* she heardВҰ127320 the newsВҰ127323 about the \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ127327\add* beingВҰ127326 takenВҰ127326, and that \add both\add* her father-in-law and her husbandВҰ127331 had died. \add вүҲAt that moment,\add* she knelt down and gave birth \add вүҲbecause the birth painsВҰ127338 suddenly started\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲBut she was dying\add*, andВҰ127340 the women who stood over her saidВҰ127342, вҖңDon't be afraidВҰ127347, because you'veВҰ127350 given birth to a son.вҖқ \add вүҲBut\add* she didn'tВҰ127345 answerВҰ127352 \add вүҲor pay any attentionВҰ127343\add*.
\v 21 She named the boyВҰ127359 вҖҳIkabodвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳno gloryвҖҷ)\add*, saying, вҖңThe glory has departed from YisraelВҰ127366,вҖқ about the \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ127370\add* beingВҰ127369 takenВҰ127369, and about \add the deaths of\add* her father-in-law and her husbandВҰ127375.
\v 22 ThenВҰ127377 she saidВҰ127377, вҖңTheВҰ127384 gloryВҰ127379 has departed from YisraelВҰ127380, because the \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ127383\add* has been takenВҰ127382.вҖқ
\c 5
\s1 The sacred chest gets carried to Ashdod
\rem /s1 The Philistines and the Ark; The Ark in Philistia; The Ark in Ashdod and Ekron; The Covenant Box among the Philistines
\p
\v 1 Now the PhilistinesВҰ127387 had taken the \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ127390\add*, and theyВҰ127388 tookВҰ127388 itВҰ127392 from Eben-Ezer to AshdodВҰ127395
\v 2 \add вүҲwhere\add* they carried \add *it\add* into the temple of \add their god\add* Dagon andВҰ127397 placedВҰ127407 it besideВҰ127409 \add a statue of\add* Dagon.
\v 3 Early the next dayВҰ127414 \add вүҲwhen\add* the Ashdodites got up, \add вүҲto their horror\add* DagonВҰ127416 had fallen to the ground on its face \add вүҲin frontВҰ127420 of\add* Yahweh's boxВҰ127421. \add вүҲSoВҰ127412\add* they \add вүҲstood it up\add* andВҰ127412 returnedВҰ127427 it to its placeВҰ127429.
\v 4 \add ButВҰ127431\add* thenВҰ127431 the next morningВҰ127432, \add вүҲmore shock\add*: DagonВҰ127435 had fallen to the ground on its face \add вүҲinВҰ127432 frontВҰ127439 of\add* Yahweh's boxВҰ127440 \add вүҲbutВҰ127431 now\add* \add *its\add* handsВҰ127447 and head were cut off, \add and were lyingВҰ127436\add* on the threshholdВҰ127451. Only \add вүҲits body remainedВҰ127454 intact\add*.
\v 5 (\add вүҲBecause of that\add*, untilВҰ127476 this dayВҰ127477 Dagon's priestsВҰ127463 andВҰ127465 everyone who enters Dagon's temple inВҰ127475 AshdodВҰ127475 won'tВҰ127460 treadВҰ127462 onВҰ127475 the threshholdВҰ127473.)
\s1 God punishes the Philistine cities
\p
\v 6 YahwehВҰ127484 \add вүҲcaused a lot of trouble\add* for the \add people of\add* AshdodВҰ127487 and he terrifiedВҰ127488 them. HeВҰ127496 \add вүҲcaused\add* them and \add вүҲthe people inВҰ127491 the region\add* to \add вүҲget lumpy growths onВҰ127491 their skin\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲWhenВҰ127501\add* the \add вүҲleaders\add* in AshdodВҰ127504 \add вүҲsaw what was happening\add*, they said, вҖңThe GodВҰ127513 of Yisrael'sВҰ127514 boxВҰ127512 mustn't stay with us because \add вүҲhe's punishing\add* \add both\add* us andВҰ127501 our god DagonВҰ127522.вҖқ
\v 8 \add вүҲSo\add* they sentВҰ127525 for all the Philistine rulersВҰ127531, andВҰ127525 \add when they'd assembled\add* they \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңWhat shouldВҰ127543 weВҰ127537 do with the god of Yisrael'sВҰ127540 box?вҖқ
\p вҖңLet the god of Yisrael's box be taken around to GatВҰ127542,вҖқ they \add вүҲdecided\add*. \add вүҲSo\add* they movedВҰ127547 \add *it\add* \add there\add*.
\v 9 After \add вүҲit arrived\add*, YahwehВҰ127563 \add вүҲstarted punishing Gat\add* and \add both\add* youngВҰ127574 and old men inВҰ127565 the city started getting growths onВҰ127565 their skin, and it caused a hugeВҰ127567 panicВҰ127566.
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ127583\add* theyВҰ127597 sentВҰ127583 God's box to EkronВҰ127588, \add вүҲbutВҰ127583\add* as soon as \add *it\add* entered \add *the city\add*, the Ekronites criedВҰ127594 out, вҖң\add Hey!\add* They've broughtВҰ127597 the godВҰ127602 of Yisrael'sВҰ127603 box here to \add вүҲkillВҰ127604 us\add* andВҰ127583 ourВҰ127607 peopleВҰ127607.вҖқ
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ127609\add* they sentВҰ127609 for the Philistine rulersВҰ127615, and \add вүҲwhen they'd assembled\add* they saidВҰ127617, вҖңSend the godВҰ127622 of Yisrael'sВҰ127623 boxВҰ127621 away. \add вүҲSend it back\add* to its placeВҰ127625 \add вүҲso\add* it won'tВҰ127626 \add вүҲcause us and our peopleВҰ127632 to die\add*.вҖқ Because there was a \add вүҲdeadly panicВҰ127636 all over\add* the cityВҰ127641 \add as\add* \add вүҲGod's punishment there was severe\add*
\v 12 andВҰ127657 the menВҰ127648 who didn'tВҰ127650 die suffered withВҰ127654 the growths. \add вүҲSoВҰ127648\add* the \add вүҲpeople's\add* cryВҰ127658 wentВҰ127657 up to the heavensВҰ127660.
\c 6
\s1 Sending the chest back to Yisrael
