\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSoВҰ127662 it was that\add* Yahweh's boxВҰ127663 was \add held\add* inВҰ127666 Philistine territoryВҰ127666 for sevenВҰ127668 monthsВҰ127669,
\v 2 thenВҰ127671 the PhilistinesВҰ127672 calledВҰ127671 \add &their\add* priestsВҰ127673 and divinersВҰ127674 and \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңWhat should we do withВҰ127682 Yahweh's boxВҰ127679? \add вүҲShow us how we can get itВҰ127683 back\add* away to itsВҰ127684 placeВҰ127684.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖңIf you're going to send the godВҰ127693 of Yisrael'sВҰ127694 boxВҰ127692 back,вҖқ they \add вүҲrespondedВҰ127686\add*, вҖңdon'tВҰ127695 send it \add вүҲback by itself\add*, butВҰ127686 definitely return it to him with a guiltВҰ127705 offeringВҰ127705. ThenВҰ127686 you'll all be healedВҰ127707, andВҰ127686 you'll all \add вүҲunderstand why you've been suffering\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 вҖңWhat guiltВҰ127719 offeringВҰ127719 should we \add вүҲsend with it\add*?вҖқ they \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p вҖңFive gold \add replicas of the\add* tumours, and five gold mice,вҖқ they said. вҖңThat's the numberВҰ127724 of \add *our\add* rulers, because \add вүҲthe same\add* plagueВҰ127736 \add вүҲaffected both them and the people\add*.
\v 5 Make replicas of the tumours and replicas of the mice that have been destroying the land, and it will honourВҰ127754 Yisrael'sВҰ127753 godВҰ127752. ThenВҰ127741 perhapsВҰ127755 he will \add вүҲless his punishment that's been\add* on you and on your godsВҰ127762 and on your land.
\v 6 Why \add вүҲhave youВҰ127767 all been so stubborn\add* just like the Egyptians when PharaohВҰ127774 made \add вүҲthem stubborn\add*? WhenВҰ127766 \add @Yisrael's god\add* dealtВҰ127780 severely with them, didn'tВҰ127778 \add @the Egyptians\add* sendВҰ127782 \add @the Israelis\add* away andВҰ127766 theyВҰ127772 wentВҰ127783?
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ127785\add* now, \add вүҲget a brand\add* new cart withВҰ127804 two nursingВҰ127793 cows \add вүҲwhichВҰ127794 have never had a yoke onВҰ127804 their necks\add*. HitchВҰ127801 the cows to the cart \add вүҲbutВҰ127785\add* take their calvesВҰ127806 \add вүҲback to their pen\add*.
\v 8 ThenВҰ127810 pick up Yahweh's box and put it into the cart \add вүҲalong with\add* the goldВҰ127823 objects thatВҰ127824 you are \add вүҲsending with it\add* as a guiltВҰ127827 offeringВҰ127827 \add вүҲput inВҰ127829 another container beside the box\add*. \add вүҲFinally\add*, sendВҰ127831 \add @the cart\add* away and \add off\add* it will goВҰ127833.
\v 9 ThenВҰ127835 watchВҰ127835 \add <it\add*. If it \add вүҲheads towards\add* Beyt-ShemeshВҰ127842 \add вүҲinВҰ127859 Israeli territory, then it's their god that caused this terrible calamity\add*. \add вүҲButВҰ127835\add* if not, then we'll knowВҰ127854 that \add вүҲit wasn't the Israeli god, andВҰ127835 that\add* it \add all\add* happenedВҰ127862 to us by chanceВҰ127860.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ127874 they followed those instructions\add*: they tookВҰ127868 twoВҰ127869 cowsВҰ127870 \add вүҲthat had been feeding calves\add* andВҰ127865 hitchedВҰ127872 them to the \add new\add* cart, butВҰ127865 they shut theirВҰ127876 calves away inВҰ127873 the \add вүҲstall\add*.
\v 11 ThenВҰ127880 theyВҰ127880 put Yahweh'sВҰ127884 boxВҰ127883 into the cart with the \add other\add* container with the goldВҰ127892 mice andВҰ127880 the replicas of theirВҰ127895 tumoursВҰ127895.
\v 12 \add Amazingly,\add* the cowsВҰ127899 wentВҰ127908 straightВҰ127897 down the roadВҰ127903 going to Beyt-Shemesh. They \add вүҲstayed onВҰ127900 that\add* one highwayВҰ127906, walking and mooing, and they \add вүҲnever once deviated to the left or the rightВҰ127914\add*, and the Philistine rulersВҰ127916 followed them as far as the borderВҰ127922 of Beyt-Shemesh.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲMeanwhile in\add* Beyt-Shemesh, \add the people\add* were harvestingВҰ127928 wheatВҰ127931 in the valleyВҰ127932, and when they \add вүҲlooked up\add* and sawВҰ127937 the boxВҰ127940, \add вүҲthey were very happy\add*.
\v 14 The cart cameВҰ127945 into the fieldВҰ127948 belonging to Yehoshua and \add then the cows just\add* stood there. There was a largeВҰ127957 stoneВҰ127956 there, and \add @the people\add* splitВҰ127958 \add the sides of\add* the wooden cart \add into pieces to start a fire\add*, then offeredВҰ127966 the cows as a burntВҰ127967 sacrifice to YahwehВҰ127968.
\v 15 Then the LevitesВҰ127971 lifted down Yahweh's boxВҰ127976 and the \add other\add* container that was with it with the goldВҰ127989 objects in it, and they placed them on the largeВҰ127994 stoneВҰ127993. Then the men of Beyt-ShemeshВҰ127998 offered up \add more\add* burntВҰ128000 offeringsВҰ128000 and sacrificed sacrifices to Yahweh on that dayВҰ128003.
\v 16 The fiveВҰ128007 Philistine rulersВҰ128008 watched \add all this from a distance before\add* returningВҰ128012 to EkronВҰ128013 that same dayВҰ128014.
\s1 The gold replicas
\p
\v 17 The goldВҰ128020 \add replicas\add* of tumours thatВҰ128021 the PhilistinesВҰ128023 sentВҰ128022 back as a guiltВҰ128024 offeringВҰ128024 to YahwehВҰ128025 were for \add the five cities\add*: AshdodВҰ128026, GazaВҰ128029, AshkelonВҰ128031, GatВҰ128033, andВҰ128018 EkronВҰ128035.
\v 18 And the gold mice were from the numberВҰ128041 of all the Philistine cities \add вүҲunder\add* the five rulersВҰ128047, includingВҰ128039 fortifiedВҰ128049 cities as \add вүҲwell\add* as the villagesВҰ128051 in the open countryВҰ128052, and as far as the largeВҰ128056 stone thatВҰ128057 they sat Yahweh's boxВҰ128061 onВҰ128066. (It's \add still\add* in Yehoshua's fieldВҰ128066 in Beyt-Shemesh untilВҰ128063 this day.)
\rem /s1 The Ark Moved to Kiriath-Jearim; The Ark at Kiriath-jearim
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲBut\add* some Beyt-ShemeshВҰ128076 men lookedВҰ128078 into Yahweh's boxВҰ128079, andВҰ128072 he killed seventyВҰ128083\f + \fr 6:19 \ft TC: The oldest Hebrew text has 50,070 men being killed here, making it hard to imagine how that many men kept clambering over dead bodies to look into the sacred chest. (But possibly we're not understanding the situation correctly?) We have followed later manuscripts here.\f* of them. The people mournedВҰ128088 because Yahweh had \add вүҲcaused such devastation\add* among the people.
\s1 The sacred chest is taken to Kiryat-Yearim
\rem /s1 The Covenant Box at Kiriath Jearim
\p
\v 20 The Beyt-ShemeshВҰ128102 men saidВҰ128098, вҖңWho can standВҰ128105 in frontВҰ128106 of the faceВҰ128106 of YahwehВҰ128107, this holy GodВҰ128108? And \add вүҲwhere should we send the box to from here\add*?вҖқ
\v 21 \add вүҲSo\add* theyВҰ128127 sentВҰ128118 messengersВҰ128119 to those living in KiriatВҰ128125-Yearim, saying, вҖңThe PhilistinesВҰ128128 have returned Yahweh's boxВҰ128131. Come \add вүҲover here andВҰ128118 get it\add*.вҖқ
\c 7
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSoВҰ128138\add* the men from KiriatВҰ128142-Yearim cameВҰ128138 and lifted up Yahweh's boxВҰ128146 and broughtВҰ128148 it into Abinadab'sВҰ128153 houseВҰ128152 onВҰ128154 the hill. They consecratedВҰ128159 his son EleazarВҰ128157 to \add вүҲtake care of\add* \add *it\add*.\x + \xo 7:1: \xt 2Sam 6:2-4; 1Ch 13:5-7.\x*
\s1 Shemuel guides Yisrael
\rem /s1 Samuel Rules Israel; Samuel Subdues the Philistines at Mizpah; Samuel judge over Israel
\p
\v 2 The \add вүҲsacred chestВҰ128170 ended up\add* staying inВҰ128171 Kiriat-Yearim for twentyВҰ128176 years \add вүҲbutВҰ128167 the IsraelisВҰ128182 longed sadly\add* for YahwehВҰ128184.
\rem /s1 Samuel Leads Israel to Victory; Samuel as Judge
\p
\v 3 Then Shemuel told all the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ128194\add*, вҖңIf you all \add really want\add* to return to Yahweh, removeВҰ128206 the foreignВҰ128210 godsВҰ128209 and the AshtoretsВҰ128212 from \add вүҲamongВҰ128211 you\add*. Then \add вүҲdecide firmly to serveВҰ128218\add* Yahweh and \add вүҲno other\add*, then he'll rescue you from the Philistines' \add вүҲoppression\add*.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ128225 the IsraelisВҰ128227\add* removedВҰ128225 the BaalВҰ128230 and AshtoretВҰ128233 \add idols\add*, and \add began to\add* serveВҰ128234 YahwehВҰ128237 only.
\p
\v 5 Then ShemuelВҰ128242 \add вүҲcalled\add*, вҖңGather all YisraelВҰ128248 to Mitspah, andВҰ128241 I'll pray to YahwehВҰ128254 for youВҰ128251 all.вҖқ
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ128256\add* they gatheredВҰ128256 at Mitspah, and drew waterВҰ128260 and pouredВҰ128261 it out \add вүҲinВҰ128278 frontВҰ128263\add* of Yahweh, and they fastedВҰ128265 onВҰ128278 that dayВҰ128266 and saidВҰ128268 thereВҰ128269, вҖңWe have sinnedВҰ128270 against Yahweh.вҖқ And ShemuelВҰ128273 \add вүҲguided\add* the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ128277\add* at Mitspah.
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲWhen\add* the Philistines heard that the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* had gatheredВҰ128284 at Mitspah, the Philistine rulersВҰ128290 \add вүҲdecided to attack\add* YisraelВҰ128287. \add вүҲWhen the Israelis\add* heard \add <that\add*, they were afraid of the Philistines
\v 8 andВҰ128303 \add вүҲbegged\add* Shemuel, вҖңDon't \add вүҲstop\add* cryingВҰ128314 out to ourВҰ128318 godВҰ128318 YahwehВҰ128317, \add вүҲso that\add* he'll rescue us from the PhilistinesВҰ128321.вҖқ
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ128323\add* ShemuelВҰ128324 got a \add вүҲyoung\add* lambВҰ128325 and offered it upвҖ”a wholeВҰ128331 burntВҰ128330 up offering to Yahweh. And \add *he\add* criedВҰ128333 out to Yahweh for YisraelВҰ128339, and Yahweh answeredВҰ128340 himВҰ128340.
\v 10 \add вүҲWhile\add* ShemuelВҰ128344 was offering up that burntВҰ128346 offering, the Philistines approached to battleВҰ128349 against YisraelВҰ128350. \add вүҲButВҰ128343\add* that dayВҰ128357 YahwehВҰ128352 \add вүҲmade an intense soundВҰ128354 like thunderВҰ128351\add* that confusedВҰ128362 the Philistines andВҰ128343 \add вүҲthe Israelis were able to defeatВҰ128363 them\add*.
\v 11 The IsraeliВҰ128369 menВҰ128368 \add вүҲran\add* out from Mitspah andВҰ128367 chased the PhilistinesВҰ128376вҖ”killing them \add вүҲall the way to\add* Beyt-Kar.
\p
\v 12 ShemuelВҰ128385 tookВҰ128384 a single rockВҰ128386 and stood it between Mitspah and ShenВҰ128393. He \add вүҲnamed\add* it вҖҳEben-EzerвҖҷ \add (which means вҖҳstoneВҰ128386 of helpвҖҷ)\add*, saying, вҖңYahwehВҰ128405 helpedВҰ128404 us \add вүҲall the way up to\add* here.вҖқ
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ128407\add* the Philistines \add вүҲended up being\add* subduedВҰ128407 and didn'tВҰ128409 invadeВҰ128413 Yisrael'sВҰ128415 border again, and YahwehВҰ128419 \add вүҲworked\add* against the Philistines \add вүҲas long as Shemuel lived\add*.
\v 14 The citiesВҰ128426 thatВҰ128427 the Philistines had takenВҰ128428 from EkronВҰ128435 and as far as GatВҰ128438 were returned to Yisrael. And \add so\add* Yisrael rescued theirВҰ128441 territoryВҰ128441 from the Philistines, and there was peaceВҰ128447 between Yisrael and the AmoritesВҰ128451.
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ128453\add* ShemuelВҰ128454 guided YisraelВҰ128457 \add вүҲwhile he lived\add*.
\v 16 \add вүҲEvery year\add* he \add вүҲdid the circuitВҰ128466\add* around Beyt-El, GilgalВҰ128470, and Mitspah, and he \add вүҲhelped settled disputes for the people inВҰ128465\add* all those placesВҰ128479,
\v 17 \add вүҲbutВҰ128482\add* he \add always\add* returnedВҰ128482 to RamahВҰ128483 because his homeВҰ128487 was there. HeВҰ128492 would \add вүҲjudgeВҰ128489 disputes\add* there, andВҰ128482 builtВҰ128493 an altarВҰ128496 to YahwehВҰ128497 there.
\c 8
\s1 The Israelis request a king
\rem /s1 The People Ask for a King; Israel Requests a King; Establishment of the monarchy; Israel Asks for a King; Israel Demands a King
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 As ShemuelВҰ128503 grew older, heВҰ128502 appointed his \add two\add* sonsВҰ128507 as judgesВҰ128508 over YisraelВҰ128509.
\v 2 The \add вүҲeldest\add* was YoelВҰ128516 andВҰ128517 \add вүҲhis brother\add* was AbiyahВҰ128519. They \add вүҲwere based\add* inВҰ128521 Be'er-Sheva.
\v 3 \add вүҲHowever,\add* they \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ128524 take afterВҰ128531 time, butВҰ128524 rather chased dishonest\add* gainвҖ”accepting bribesВҰ128535 andВҰ128524 pervertingВҰ128536 justiceВҰ128537.
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲEventually,\add* the IsraeliВҰ128542 eldersВҰ128542 met togetherВҰ128540 with Shemuel at RamahВҰ128548
\v 5 and \add вүҲrequested\add*, вҖңListen, you're old \add now\add*, and your sonsВҰ128555 don'tВҰ128556 \add вүҲfollow your example\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ128550\add* appointВҰ128560 a kingВҰ128563 for us now to \add вүҲlead\add* us like all the other nationsВҰ128567.вҖқ\x + \xo 8:5: \xt Deu 17:14.\x*
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ128569\add* ShemuelВҰ128572 \add вүҲthought that their request for a kingВҰ128578 was an evil request, so\add* \add *he\add* prayedВҰ128580 to YahwehВҰ128584
\v 7 \add вүҲwho replied\add*, вҖңListen to \add вүҲeverything that the peopleВҰ128594 are saying\add*, because they're not rejecting \em you\em*, butВҰ128587 they're rejecting me from reigningВҰ128608 over them.
\v 8 They're doingВҰ128631 to you just what they've done to me every since I \add вүҲrescued\add* them out of EgyptВҰ128620 and right up until today: desertingВҰ128625 me and servingВҰ128626 otherВҰ128628 godsВҰ128627.
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ128636\add* listenВҰ128637 to \add вүҲwhat they're saying\add* now, butВҰ128636 certainlyВҰ128642 warn them about \add вүҲwhat kings require of theirВҰ128638 subjects\add*.вҖқ
\s1 Advance warnings about having a king
\rem /s1 Samuel Warns against a Kingdom
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 10 Then ShemuelВҰ128655 \add вүҲpassed on everything that YahwehВҰ128660 had said\add* to the peopleВҰ128663 who were requesting a king from him,
\v 11 telling them, вҖң\add вүҲIfВҰ128677 you all have a kingВҰ128673 reigningВҰ128675 over you, this is what he'll demand\add*: he will \add вүҲconscript\add* your sonsВҰ128679 and appointВҰ128681 them \add вүҲas his cavalry or charioteers, or they'll runВҰ128685 as foot-soldiers inВҰ128683 frontВҰ128686\add*, of his chariotВҰ128687.
\v 12 \add вүҲOthers he'll appointВҰ128689 a commander of various units\add*. \add вүҲSome will end up ploughing his fields or harvestingВҰ128698 his crops, or manufacturing his weaponsВҰ128700 andВҰ128689 chariotsВҰ128704\add*.
\v 13 He'll takeВҰ128709 yourВҰ128708 daughtersВҰ128708 to \add вүҲmanufacture perfumesВҰ128710\add*, or to be cooksВҰ128711 andВҰ128706 bakersВҰ128712.
\v 14 He'll confiscate your \add вүҲbest\add* fieldsВҰ128716 and vineyardsВҰ128719 and oliveВҰ128720 orchardsВҰ128720, and give to his servantsВҰ128724 \add to control\add*.
\v 15 ThenВҰ128726 he'll demand a tenth of your seedsВҰ128726 and \add вүҲgrape harvests for\add* his officialsВҰ128730 and his servantsВҰ128731.
\v 16 He'll commandeer \add some of\add* your \add вүҲbest\add* male and femaleВҰ128738 servants and youngВҰ128741 menВҰ128741, and he'll impound \add some of\add* your donkeysВҰ128745, thenВҰ128733 he'll use \add them all\add* for his \add вүҲprojects\add*.
\v 17 He'll \add вүҲexpect\add* a tenth of your \add вүҲsheep and goats\add*, and you yourselves \add вүҲwill end up being\add* his slaves.
\v 18 \add вүҲWhenВҰ128770 that all happens\add*, you'll all cryВҰ128758 out \add вүҲin front\add* of the kingВҰ128762 who you choseВҰ128764 for yourselves, \add вүҲbutВҰ128758\add* YahwehВҰ128769 won'tВҰ128766 be answeringВҰ128768 you \add вүҲat that time\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Israel's Request for a King Granted
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the peopleВҰ128775 refusedВҰ128774 to \add вүҲconsider Shemuel's advice\add* andВҰ128779 theyВҰ128779 \add вүҲargued\add*, вҖңNo, \add вүҲwe want\add* a kingВҰ128784 over us
\v 20 \add вүҲso\add* we'll be like all the other nationsВҰ128794. OurВҰ128800 kingВҰ128796 will judgeВҰ128795 us, andВҰ128788 will \add вүҲlead out our warriors in battleВҰ128802\add*.вҖқ
\v 21 ShemuelВҰ128805 listenedВҰ128804 to \add вүҲeverything the peopleВҰ128810 said, andВҰ128811 passed it onВҰ128812 to\add* YahwehВҰ128813,
\v 22 and YahwehВҰ128817 told \add *him\add*, вҖң\add вүҲDo what they're asking and get them\add* a kingВҰ128825.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* ShemuelВҰ128820 \add told the peopleВҰ128830 and then sent them all back to theirВҰ128822 homes\add*.
\c 9
\s1 Sha'ul is chosen as king
\rem /s1 Saul Meets Samuel; Samuel Anoints Saul; Saul Chosen to Be King
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* there was a Benyamite man named KishВҰ128846 (son of AbielВҰ128849, son of ZerorВҰ128852, son of Bekorath, son of AfiahВҰ128858, the son of a YaminiteВҰ128862 man) \add вүҲwho was strong and wealthyВҰ128864\add*.
\v 2 \add @Kish\add* had a son \add вүҲnamed\add* Sha'ulВҰ128871 who was a handsomeВҰ128873 youngВҰ128872 man and goodвҖ”\add вүҲin fact thereВҰ128874 wasn't any IsraeliВҰ128877 man\add* better than him, \add and\add* he was \add вүҲhead and shouldersВҰ128880 taller than anyone else\add*.
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲOne time,\add* the female donkeys of Sha'uls fatherВҰ128890 Kish \add вүҲhad gone missing\add*, and Kish \add вүҲtold\add* his son, вҖңTake one of the servantsВҰ128905 with youВҰ128901, and \add вүҲpack up\add* and goВҰ128907 and find those donkeys.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ128913\add* \add #they\add* passed through the Efrayimite hill countryВҰ128914, thenВҰ128913 through the ShalishahВҰ128920 \add вүҲregion\add*, but they didn't find them. ThenВҰ128913 they went through the ShaalimВҰ128926 \add вүҲregion\add*, but thereВҰ128927 was nothing, \add вүҲso\add* \add #they\add* \add вүҲcontinued onВҰ128914\add* through the land of the Benyamites, but they didn't find them.
\v 5 \add Finally,\add* theyВҰ128936 entered the Tsuf \add вүҲarea\add*, and \add eventually\add* Sha'ulВҰ128939 saidВҰ128940 to his servantВҰ128941, вҖңCome on. Let's \add вүҲgoВҰ128946 back home in case\add* my fatherВҰ128950 \add вүҲstops worrying\add* about the donkeysВҰ128953 and \add starts\add* worrying about us.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ128957\add* he \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңListen, pleaseВҰ128961. There's an honouredВҰ128968 man of GodВҰ128964 inВҰ128965 this cityВҰ128965. \add вүҲEverything he says comesВҰ128974 true\add*. Let's go thereВҰ128977 now. Perhaps he'll tell us \add вүҲwhichВҰ128984 way we shouldВҰ128976 have gone\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖң\add вүҲOkay, thenВҰ128989.\add* We can go \add thereВҰ129003\add*,вҖқ Sha'ulВҰ128990 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ128989\add*, вҖңbutВҰ128989 what \add вүҲcan we give\add* the man? \add вүҲWe don'tВҰ129003 have any more food in our bags, andВҰ128989 we never brought along a giftВҰ129002. What else do we have?\add*вҖқ
\p
\v 8 вҖңLook,вҖқ answeredВҰ129013 the servantВҰ129012, вҖңI've got a \add вүҲsmall silverВҰ129023 coin\add*. We can giveВҰ129024 that to the manВҰ129025 andВҰ129011 he'll tell us where to go.вҖқ
\v 9 (In YisraelВҰ129035 before then, \add вүҲwhen people wanted an answer from\add* GodВҰ129042, they'd say, вҖңCome andВҰ129044 let us goВҰ129044 to the вҖҳseerвҖҷ,вҖқ because the prophetВҰ129049 of today was calledВҰ129051 the вҖҳseerвҖҷ before.)
\p
\v 10 вҖң\add вүҲGood idea\add*,вҖқ Sha'ulВҰ129056 told his servantВҰ129057. вҖңLet's goВҰ129062 thenВҰ129055.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ129055\add* theyВҰ129063 wentВҰ129063 to the cityВҰ129066 thereВҰ129069 whereВҰ129067 the manВҰ129070 of GodВҰ129071 was.
\v 11 They were \add вүҲclimbing up the rise towards\add* the cityВҰ129076 \add вүҲwhen\add* they \add вүҲmet some\add* youngВҰ129079 womenВҰ129079 goingВҰ129074 out to draw waterВҰ129082, and they \add вүҲasked\add* them, вҖңIs the seer inВҰ129075 \add вүҲtownВҰ129076\add*?вҖқ
\v 12 вҖң\add вүҲYes he is\add*,вҖқ they answeredВҰ129089. вҖңHurry \add вүҲthough\add*, because he's comeВҰ129100 to the cityВҰ129101 today \add to offer\add* the sacrificeВҰ129103 for the peopleВҰ129105 atВҰ129106 the highВҰ129106 placeВҰ129106.
\v 13 You'll find him as soon as you enterВҰ129108 the cityВҰ129109, beforeВҰ129113 he goes up to the high placeВҰ129115 to eat. The peopleВҰ129121 won'tВҰ129118 eat untilВҰ129122 he \add вүҲgets there\add*, because he himself will blessВҰ129128 the sacrificeВҰ129129. Afterwards, \add вүҲthoseВҰ129134 who've been invitedВҰ129134\add* will eat \add together there\add*. So go up there now \add вүҲand you'll soon find him\add*.вҖқ
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ129144\add* they went on up into the city, andВҰ129144 as they were entering, wow, there was ShemuelВҰ129151 \add вүҲcoming out towardsВҰ129153\add* them to go up to the high placeВҰ129155.
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲOnВҰ129169 the previous dayВҰ129164,\add* YahwehВҰ129158 \add вүҲhad quietly told\add* ShemuelВҰ129163,
\v 16 вҖңAboutВҰ129172 this time tomorrowВҰ129174, I'llВҰ129175 send a Benyamite manВҰ129177 to you, and you should anointВҰ129180 him to be rulerВҰ129181 over my people YisraelВҰ129185. He will \add вүҲrescue\add* my people from the PhilistinesВҰ129191, because I'veВҰ129193 \add вүҲnoticed\add* my people because \add вүҲI heard theirВҰ129199 cries\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ129202 Shemuel sawВҰ129203 Sha'ulВҰ129206, andВҰ129207 YahwehВҰ129207 told himВҰ129208, вҖңLook, \add that's\add* the manВҰ129210 that I youВҰ129213 \add about\add*. \add вүҲHe\add* will \add help control\add* my peopleВҰ129216.вҖқ
\v 18 \add вүҲAs\add* Sha'ulВҰ129219 approachedВҰ129218 ShemuelВҰ129222 \add вүҲright there in the middleВҰ129223 of the city gateway\add*, he \add вүҲaskedВҰ129225\add*, вҖңPlease tell me, where'sВҰ129230 the seer'sВҰ129234 houseВҰ129233?вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңI am the seer,вҖқ ShemuelВҰ129237 answeredВҰ129236, вҖң\add Now,\add* Go up to the highВҰ129246 placeВҰ129246 \add вүҲahead of me\add*, andВҰ129236 you'll eatВҰ129247 withВҰ129251 me today. In the morningВҰ129251, I'll tell you \add вүҲwhat you want to know\add*, thenВҰ129236 I'll sendВҰ129250 you off.
\v 20 As for your donkeysВҰ129258 thatВҰ129259 were lost threeВҰ129262 daysВҰ129263 ago, don'tВҰ129264 \add вүҲworry anymore about them\add* because they'veВҰ129272 been foundВҰ129272. Now, all of YisraelВҰ129277 is wanting your father's \add вүҲhouseholdВҰ129281\add*, andВҰ129258 \add вүЎwanting\add* you \add in particular\add*.вҖқ
\v 21 вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ129285\add* I'm a Benyamite,вҖқ Sha'ulВҰ129286 respondedВҰ129285, вҖң\add That's\add* the smallestВҰ129293 tribe in YisraelВҰ129296, and my clan's the lowliestВҰ129298 of all the Benyamite clansВҰ129301. \add вүҲSo\add* why \add вүҲdid youВҰ129305 talk to me like that\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 22 Then Shemuel tookВҰ129311 Sha'ulВҰ129315 and his servantВҰ129318 to the roomВҰ129323 \add where the meal had been prepared\add*, and he gaveВҰ129321 them a placeВҰ129323 atВҰ129324 the headВҰ129324 of \add вүҲtableвҖ”even above the invitedВҰ129325 guests\add*. (There were aboutВҰ129327 thirtyВҰ129327 men.)
\v 23 And ShemuelВҰ129331 told the cook, вҖңGive the \add special\add* \add вүҲpiece of meat\add* thatВҰ129337 I \add вүҲshowed\add* you andВҰ129330 said to keep aside.вҖқ
\v 24 \add вүҲSo\add* the cook liftedВҰ129347 the \add вүҲcooked leg\add* andВҰ129347 \add вүҲplaced it in frontВҰ129355\add* of Sha'ul. ThenВҰ129347 \add &ShemuelВҰ129377\add* told \add Sha'ul\add*, вҖңLook, \add вүҲthis has been reserved for you\add*. Eat \add <it\add*, because it's been keptВҰ129366 \add вүҲuntil\add* the appointedВҰ129365 timeВҰ129365 \add вүҲwhen I could call these peopleВҰ129370 together\add*.вҖқ
\s1 Shemuel anoints Sha'ul with oil
\s4 Full kingdom
\p \add вүҲSo\add* Sha'ul ateВҰ129373 with Shemuel thatВҰ129359 dayВҰ129378,
\v 25 and thenВҰ129381 theyВҰ129381 wentВҰ129381 \add back\add* from the highВҰ129382 placeВҰ129382 down into the cityВҰ129383, and \add @Shemuel\add* spokeВҰ129384 with Sha'ulВҰ129387 on \add his house\add* roofВҰ129390.
\p
\v 26 They rose earlyВҰ129392 \add the next day\add*. At dawn, ShemuelВҰ129397 had calledВҰ129396 to Sha'ul on the roofВҰ129401, saying, вҖңGet up and I will sendВҰ129405 youВҰ129405 \add вүҲoff\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ129392\add* Sha'ul got up, and the two of them wentВҰ129408 outsideВҰ129412.
\rem /s1 Samuel Anoints Saul as Ruler; Samuel Anoints Saul
\v 27 \add When\add* they \add вүҲreached\add* the edge of the cityВҰ129417, Shemuel saidВҰ129419 to Sha'ulВҰ129422, вҖң\add вүҲTell your servantВҰ129424 to goВҰ129425 on ahead\add*,вҖқ and \add so\add* he wentВҰ129427 on ahead. вҖңButВҰ129418 you stand \add вүҲhere\add*, and I'll \add вүҲgive you the messageВҰ129434 from\add* GodВҰ129435.вҖқ
\c 10
\rem /s1 Samuel Anoints Saul as King
\p
\v 1 Then ShemuelВҰ129439 tookВҰ129438 a flaskВҰ129442 of oilВҰ129443, and pouredВҰ129444 it on \add @Sha'ul's\add* headВҰ129447 and kissedВҰ129448 him, and told him, вҖңIt's YahwehВҰ129454 who has anointedВҰ129453 you to be rulerВҰ129458 over his \add вүҲchosen people\add*.
\v 2 \add вүҲAfter you leave me today\add* \add and get back to\add* Benyamite territoryВҰ129470, then you'll \add вүҲsee\add* two menВҰ129465 near Rachel'sВҰ129469 tomb inВҰ129470 Tseltsah, and they'll say to you, вҖҳThe donkeys thatВҰ129477 you wentВҰ129478 to look for have been foundВҰ129475. \add вүҲButВҰ129463\add*, wow, your father has stopped worryingВҰ129487 about the donkeys and \add now\add* he's worried about \em you\em* \add вүҲand trying to figure out what he should do\add*.вҖҷ
\v 3 ThenВҰ129494 furtherВҰ129496 on from there, \add вүҲas you approach\add* the oak treeВҰ129500 at TaborВҰ129501, you'll find three menВҰ129505 goingВҰ129506 to Beyt-El to worship GodВҰ129509. OneВҰ129510 will be taking three young goats, one will be carrying three roundsВҰ129521 loavesВҰ129521 of breadВҰ129522, andВҰ129494 one will be carrying a wine in a container.
\v 4 They'll askВҰ129529 about \add вүҲhow you're doing\add* andВҰ129529 giveВҰ129532 you twoВҰ129534 loaves of breadВҰ129536 which you should acceptВҰ129537.
\v 5 AfterВҰ129540 that, you'll come to the hill of GodВҰ129544 (whereВҰ129545 there's a camp of Philistine \add warriors\add*). \add вүҲWhen you enter\add* the townВҰ129553, you'll meet a group of prophetsВҰ129556 descending from the \add вүҲaltar area\add*,
\v 6 and Yahweh'sВҰ129570 spiritВҰ129569 will rush onto you. ThenВҰ129567 you'll \add join\add* them in prophesyingВҰ129571, and you'll be transformed into a different personВҰ129574.
\v 7 \add вүҲWhenВҰ129577 this all comes true\add*, do whatever you think is correct because GodВҰ129590 \add вүҲwill be helping\add* you.
\v 8 ThenВҰ129593 goВҰ129593 \add вүҲahead of me\add* to GilgalВҰ129595 and wait \add there\add* for sevenВҰ129605 daysВҰ129606, untilВҰ129608 I get there and tell you what to do. I'llВҰ129612 join you to offer burntВҰ129601 offerings \add and\add* to sacrificeВҰ129602 peaceВҰ129604 offerings.
\rem /s1 Saul Prophesies; Saul Made King; Samuel's Signs Are Fulfilled
\p
\v 9 Then as Sha'ul \add вүҲstarted to leave\add* Shemuel, GodВҰ129627 \add вүҲchangedВҰ129624 his thinking\add*. Then all Shemuel's predictions cameВҰ129630 true that dayВҰ129635,
\v 10 \add вүҲso when\add* \add @Sha'ul and his servant\add* cameВҰ129639 to the hill, a group of prophets met \add #them\add* and God'sВҰ129641 spiritВҰ129649 rushedВҰ129647 onto \add @Sha'ul\add* and he \add вүҲjoined them inВҰ129652\add* prophesying.
\v 11 ThenВҰ129654 everyoneВҰ129655 who had known \add @Sha'ul\add* \add вүҲpreviously\add* heard himВҰ129657 prophesying withВҰ129681 the prophets, \add вүҲtheyВҰ129660 asked each other\add*, вҖңWhat's happenedВҰ129675 to Kish'sВҰ129678 son? Is Sha'ul really a prophet \add now\add*?вҖқ
\v 12 A manВҰ129684 from thereВҰ129685 answeredВҰ129683, вҖңAnd who is \em theirВҰ129688\em* fatherВҰ129688?вҖқ SoВҰ129683 after that it becameВҰ129692 a common saying, вҖңHas Sha'ulВҰ129695 also \add вүҲbecome a prophetВҰ129696\add*?вҖқ\x + \xo 10:12: \xt 1Sam 19:23-24.\x*
\v 13 WhenВҰ129698 he had finished prophesyingВҰ129699, he ascended to the \add вүҲaltar area\add*.
\p
\v 14 \add Later,\add* Sha'ul'sВҰ129705 uncleВҰ129704 asked him andВҰ129703 his servantВҰ129709, вҖңWhere did youВҰ129711 \add two\add* \add вүҲtake off to\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңTo lookВҰ129713 for the donkeysВҰ129716,вҖқ Sha'ul replied. вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ129703 we couldn't find them, so\add* we wentВҰ129721 to ShemuelВҰ129724.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖң\add вүҲAnd what did he tell you?\add*вҖқ \add *the\add* uncleВҰ129727 \add вүҲasked\add*.
\p
\v 16 вҖңHe \add вүҲassured\add* us that the donkeysВҰ129749 had been foundВҰ129748,вҖқ Sha'ulВҰ129740 replied. \add вүҲButВҰ129739\add* he didn'tВҰ129754 tell him anything that ShemuelВҰ129760 had said \add вүҲabout becoming king\add*.
\s1 Sha'ul is selected as king
\rem /s1 Saul Proclaimed King; Saul Is Acclaimed King; Saul Is Acclaimed as King
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 17 Then ShemuelВҰ129764 summonedВҰ129763 the peopleВҰ129767 \add to come before\add* YahwehВҰ129770 at Mitspah,
\v 18 and he told \add *them\add*, вҖңYahwehВҰ129783, the godВҰ129784 of Yisrael, saysВҰ129782, вҖҳI myself broughtВҰ129787 Yisrael out of EgyptВҰ129791. I rescued you from \add вүҲEgyptian control\add*, and from all the kingdomsВҰ129799 thatВҰ129800 oppressedВҰ129800 you.вҖҷ
\v 19 \add вүҲButВҰ129803 since thenВҰ129803\add*, you all have rejectedВҰ129805 your godВҰ129808вҖ”the one who saves you from all your calamitiesВҰ129816 and distressesВҰ129817. And you've all saidВҰ129818 to him, вҖҳ\add вүҲWe'd rather have\add* a kingВҰ129822 over us.вҖҷ \add вүҲSoВҰ129803\add* station yourselvesВҰ129826 now \add вүҲin frontВҰ129827\add* of YahwehВҰ129828 by your tribesВҰ129829 and \add вүҲclansВҰ129830\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ129832 ShemuelВҰ129833 had all the IsraeliВҰ129838 tribes approach, andВҰ129839 the tribe of BenyaminВҰ129841 was selected.
\v 21 Then he had all the Benyamite clans approach, and the MatriВҰ129852 clan was selected. Then Kish'sВҰ129857 son, Sha'ulВҰ129854 was selected and they tried to find him, butВҰ129843 \add вүҲthey couldn't find him anywhere\add*
\v 22 \add вүҲso\add* theyВҰ129862 asked Yahweh againВҰ129864, вҖң\add вүҲIs that manВҰ129869 around here anywhere\add*?вҖқ
\p вҖңLook, he's hidingВҰ129876 among the supplies,вҖқ Yahweh \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲSoВҰ129881\add* they ran and got him from thereВҰ129883, and \add when\add* he took his place among the people, he was head and shouldersВҰ129891 tallerВҰ129887 than anyone else.
\v 24 ThenВҰ129894 Shemuel \add вүҲannounced to everyoneВҰ129900\add*, вҖңCan you see the one that YahwehВҰ129906 has chosenВҰ129903? Certainly there'sВҰ129908 no one else like him among all the people.вҖқ
\p All the people saw \add <that\add* andВҰ129894 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ129894\add*, вҖң\add вүҲLong\add* live the kingВҰ129919.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 Then ShemuelВҰ129923 \add вүҲexplained\add* how the kingshipВҰ129929 would work, and wroteВҰ129930 it in a book and placedВҰ129932 it \add вүҲin frontВҰ129933\add* of YahwehВҰ129934. Then \add *he\add* sentВҰ129935 \add вүҲeveryoneВҰ129926 homeВҰ129943\add*.
\v 26 ShemuelВҰ129947 also went \add вүҲhomeВҰ129949\add* to GibeahВҰ129950, \add вүҲaccompanied by some of\add* the powerful \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ129953\add* whoseВҰ129958 heartsВҰ129958 GodВҰ129957 had touchedВҰ129956.
\v 27 \add вүҲButВҰ129960 some worthlessВҰ129961 men asked\add*, вҖңHow can that one saveВҰ129965 us?вҖқ and they despisedВҰ129967 \add @Sha'ul\add* and didn'tВҰ129968 bring himВҰ129967 any gifts, butВҰ129960 he \add вүҲmade no comment\add*.
\c 11
\s1 Sha'ul rescues Yabesh from the Ammonites
\rem /s1 Saul Rescues the City of Jabesh; Saul Defeats the Ammonites
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add About a month later,\add*\f + \fr 11:1 \ft This appears only in a few ancient documents.\f* NahashВҰ129978 the AmmoniteВҰ129979 \add took his menВҰ129988\add* and camped \add вүҲaround\add* Yabesh-GileadВҰ129984, and the \add вүҲleaders\add* of Yabesh told \add *him\add*, вҖң\add вүҲMake a treaty with\add* us, and we'll serveВҰ129997 youВҰ129997.вҖқ
\p
\v 2 вҖң\add YesВҰ130002,\add* I'llВҰ130004 \add вүҲmake an treaty withВҰ130003\add* you,вҖқ NahashВҰ130001 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖңby gougingВҰ130006 out \add вүҲall of your\add* rightВҰ130011 \add #eyes\add* \add вүҲinВҰ130003 order to shame\add* all YisraelВҰ130018.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖң\add Oh! ThenВҰ130020\add* leave us alone for sevenВҰ130026 daysВҰ130027,вҖқ the YabeshВҰ130023 eldersВҰ130022 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ130020\add*, вҖңso that we can sendВҰ130028 messengersВҰ130029 through all the territoryВҰ130031 of YisraelВҰ130032. If no one \add вүҲwill comeВҰ130038 to rescue\add* us, thenВҰ130020 we'll \add вүҲsurrenderВҰ130038\add* to youВҰ130039.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲWhenВҰ130053\add* the messengersВҰ130042 arrived \add вүҲwhere Sha'ulВҰ130044 lived\add* atВҰ130047 GibeahВҰ130043 andВҰ130041 \add вүҲpassed the news onto the people\add*, \add вүҲeveryoneВҰ130048 started wailing loudly\add*.
\v 5 \add вүҲAt that time\add*, Sha'ulВҰ130059 was walking home behind the cattleВҰ130062 andВҰ130058 \add *he\add* asked, вҖңWhat's with \add all\add* the peopleВҰ130070 wailing?вҖқ ThenВҰ130058 theyВҰ130072 \add вүҲtold\add* him \add вүҲwhat the messengers from YabeshВҰ130080 had saidВҰ130066\add*.
\v 6 God'sВҰ130091 spiritВҰ130083 rushedВҰ130082 onВҰ130089 Sha'ulВҰ130088 as he heardВҰ130089 the messageВҰ130093, andВҰ130082 \add вүҲhe became very angry\add*.
\v 7 Then he tookВҰ130099 a pair of cattle and \add вүҲchopped\add* them into piecesВҰ130102, and sentВҰ130103 messengersВҰ130109 to take them \add вүҲthroughout\add* YisraelВҰ130107 and \add вүҲannounce\add*, вҖңThis is what will be done to the cattle of \add вүҲanyoneВҰ130131 who doesn't join\add* Sha'ulВҰ130116 and Shemuel \add inВҰ130108 battle\add*.вҖқ
\p Then YahwehВҰ130125 \add вүҲcaused the peopleВҰ130128 to be afraid of him\add*, and they united together.
\v 8 \add вүҲWhenВҰ130133\add* \add @Sha'ul\add* assembled them atВҰ130134 BezekВҰ130134, there were threeВҰ130139 hundredВҰ130140 thousand \add warriorsВҰ130142\add* from YisraelВҰ130138 andВҰ130133 thirtyВҰ130144 thousand from YehudahВҰ130143,
\v 9 and they told the \add original\add* messengers, вҖң\add Go and\add* \add вүҲtell the leaders\add* of YabeshВҰ130167-Gilead, вҖҳTomorrow you'll all \add вүҲbe rescued\add* \add вүҲby the time that\add* the sun's \add вүҲatВҰ130160 its hottest\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ130170\add* the YabeshВҰ130172 \add вүҲleaders told\add* \add Nahash\add*, вҖң\add вүҲWe'll surrender\add* to you all tomorrowВҰ130173, thenВҰ130170 you can do to us \add вүҲwhateverВҰ130178 seems goodВҰ130180 to you all\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 The next day, Sha'ulВҰ130187 divided \add &his\add* warriors into threeВҰ130191 divisions, and they \add вүҲattacked the Ammonite campВҰ130196 before the sun rose\add*. Then they \add вүҲslaughtered the AmmonitesВҰ130202\add* untilВҰ130203 the hottest part of the day. \add &Their\add* remainingВҰ130211 warriors were scatteredВҰ130209 \add вүҲso completely that no two of them were able to stay\add* togetherВҰ130215.
\s1 Sha'ul reaffirmed as king
\rem /s1 Saul Confirmed as King
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ130217 the peopleВҰ130218 \add вүҲasked\add* ShemuelВҰ130221, вҖңWho \add вүҲwere the ones saying that Sha'ulВҰ130224 wasn't fit to\add* reignВҰ130225 over us? \add вүҲBring them here\add* andВҰ130229 we'll \add вүҲexecute\add* them.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 вҖң\add вүҲNo one's going to be executed\add* today,вҖқ Sha'ulВҰ130232 saidВҰ130231, вҖңbecause today YahwehВҰ130243 has \add вүҲrescued\add* YisraelВҰ130245.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖңCome \add on then\add*,вҖқ saidВҰ130248 ShemuelВҰ130249. вҖңLet's goВҰ130254 to GilgalВҰ130255 and renewВҰ130256 the kingship thereВҰ130257.вҖқ
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ130260\add* all the people when to GilgalВҰ130264 and \add вүҲinВҰ130272 frontВҰ130270\add* of Yahweh they \add вүҲreaffirmed Sha'ul as kingВҰ130265\add*. ThenВҰ130260 they offered sacrificesВҰ130273 \add as\add* peaceВҰ130277 offeringsВҰ130277 \add вүҲto\add* Yahweh, thenВҰ130260 Sha'ul and the people \add вүҲcelebrated together\add*.
\c 12
\s1 Shemuel's farewell speech
\rem /s1 Samuel's Farewell Speech; Samuel Addresses the People; Samuel's Farewell Address
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 Then ShemuelВҰ130293 said to all YisraelВҰ130298, вҖң\add вүҲListen to me now.\add* I've listenedВҰ130300 to your voicesВҰ130301 \add вүҲand taken notice of everything\add* that you all said to me. And I've \add вүҲappointed\add* a king to reign over you all.
\v 2 \add вүҲSoВҰ130311 look now and you can see your king walkingВҰ130315 here in front of you all\add*. \add вүҲButВҰ130311 as for me,\add* I'm old and gray, and my sons are among you all. I'veВҰ130324 \add вүҲserved you all openly\add* from my youthВҰ130326 right up to the present time,
\v 3 \add and\add* here I am now. \add вүҲNow withВҰ130334 YahwehВҰ130336 listening, answer this truthfully\add*: Have I \add ever\add* taken anyone's ox or donkeyВҰ130345? Did I cheat anyone? Have I oppressedВҰ130351 anyone or taken a bribe \add вүҲto not see something\add*? I'llВҰ130361 pay back anything I owe \add anyone\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 вҖң\add No,\add* you haven't cheated us,вҖқ they \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖңAnd you haven't oppressedВҰ130371 us or takenВҰ130374 \add вүҲany payments\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҖңYahwehВҰ130383 is a \add вүҲyour\add* witness,вҖқ he said. вҖңAnd his anointedВҰ130386 \add king\add* is a witness today, that you have \add вүҲnever foundВҰ130391 me taking anythingВҰ130393 that wasn't mine\add*.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add вүҲWe witness that\add*,вҖқ \add #they\add* \add вүҲagreed\add*.
\p
\v 6 вҖңIt was YahwehВҰ130403 who appointedВҰ130405 MoshehВҰ130408 and AharonВҰ130411,вҖқ Shemuel continuedВҰ130398, вҖңand who broughtВҰ130413 yourВҰ130416 ancestorsВҰ130416 out of EgyptВҰ130418.\x + \xo 12:6: \xt Exo 6:26.\x*
\v 7 Now presentВҰ130421 yourselvesВҰ130421 to YahwehВҰ130425 as I confront you all in \add вүҲfrontВҰ130424\add* of \add *him\add* \add by telling you about\add* \add *his\add* righteousnessВҰ130429 thatВҰ130431 he \add вүҲdisplayed to\add* you all \add вүҲas well as\add* to your ancestorsВҰ130437 \add before you\add*:
\v 8 AfterВҰ130439 YacobВҰ130442 went to Egypt and your ancestors criedВҰ130444 out to Yahweh, then Yahweh sent MoshehВҰ130453 and AharonВҰ130456, and they broughtВҰ130457 your ancestors out of Egypt and settledВҰ130462 them into this placeВҰ130463.\x + \xo 12:8: \xt Exo 2:23.\x*
\v 9 Then they forgotВҰ130466 theirВҰ130470 godВҰ130470 YahwehВҰ130469, and he \add вүҲallowed them to be oppressed by\add* SiseraВҰ130474 (the commanderВҰ130475 of the army from HazorВҰ130478), and the PhilistinesВҰ130481, and the kingВҰ130483 of MoabВҰ130484. Then they foughtВҰ130485 againstВҰ130486 them\x + \xo 12:9: a \xt Jdg 4:2; \xo b \xt Jdg 13:1; \xo c \xt Jdg 3:12.\x*
\v 10 and criedВҰ130488 out to Yahweh, вҖҳWe have sinnedВҰ130495, because we've abandonedВҰ130497 Yahweh and have servedВҰ130501 the BaalsВҰ130504 and the AshtoretsВҰ130507. \add вүҲButВҰ130488 if\add* you rescue us now from our enemiesВҰ130511, we will serveВҰ130512 you.вҖҷ\x + \xo 12:10: \xt Jdg 10:10-15.\x*
