\v 47 \add вүҲAfter\add* Sha'ulВҰ132181 had takenВҰ132182 onВҰ132193 the kingship of YisraelВҰ132186, he foughtВҰ132187 against their enemies from all aroundВҰ132188: against the Moabites, the AmmonitesВҰ132197, the Edomites, the kingsВҰ132199 of ZobahВҰ132200, andВҰ132181 against the PhilistinesВҰ132201. Wherever he turnedВҰ132205, he punished \add his enemies\add*.
\v 48 He acted bravely andВҰ132208 \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ132210\add* \add even\add* the Amalekites, \add always\add* rescuingВҰ132214 YisraelВҰ132217 from thoseВҰ132219 who \add came in to\add* plunderВҰ132219 it.
