\v 32 Then ShemuelВҰ132873 \add вүҲcommanded\add*, вҖңBring the Amalekite KingВҰ132879 AgagВҰ132878 over here to me.вҖқ
\p \add вүҲSo\add* they \add brought\add* him over, and trembling,\f + \fr 15:32 \ft The meaning of the original word here is unclear and so there'll be different interpretations.\f* he said, вҖң\add вүҲI've faced up to deathВҰ132891 now\add*.вҖқ\f + \fr 15:32 \ft Some translations interpret the original words as Agag thinking (or saying to himself) that he was going to be spared, but he surely knew Shemuel.\f*
\p
\v 33 Then ShemuelВҰ132906 told \add him\add*,
\q1 вҖңJust as your swordВҰ132899 has made women childless,
