\v 37 Then \add *he\add* added, вҖңYahweh who has saved me from the lionВҰ134073 and from the bear, \em he\em* will \add be the one to\add* save me from that PhilistineВҰ134079.вҖқ
\p вҖңGo \add then\add*, and Yahweh be with you.вҖқ Sha'ulВҰ134083 \add вүҲassented\add*.
\v 38 ThenВҰ134092 Sha'ulВҰ134093 \add had\add* DavidВҰ134096 dressed in his \add own battle\add* attire, andВҰ134092 thenВҰ134092 in bodyВҰ134106 armourВҰ134106 with a bronzeВҰ134100 helmetВҰ134099.
\v 39 DavidВҰ134109 strappedВҰ134108 his swordВҰ134112 over \add вүҲthe top\add* andВҰ134108 thenВҰ134108 triedВҰ134115 to walk because he hadn't been trained \add in wearing it\add*. \add вүҲButВҰ134108\add* \add *he\add* told Sha'ulВҰ134125, вҖңI \add вүҲcouldn't walk in all that without practice\add*,вҖқ \add вүҲso\add* he tookВҰ134133 it \add all\add* off.
\v 40 ThenВҰ134137 he \add вүҲpicked up\add* his staffВҰ134138, and selected fiveВҰ134143 smoothВҰ134144 stonesВҰ134146 from the riverbed. HeВҰ134152 placed them inВҰ134153 the pouchВҰ134158 of his shepherd'sВҰ134154 bag, and \add вүҲpicked up\add* his slingВҰ134159 and \add вүҲheaded towards\add* the PhilistineВҰ134164 \add champion\add*.
\s1 David fronts up to Goliat
