\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 55 When Sha'ulВҰ134450 had seen DavidВҰ134453 goingВҰ134454 out to meet \add @Goliat\add*, he'd \add вүҲasked\add* Abner, the army commanderВҰ134461, вҖңWhose son is this lad, Abner?вҖқ
\p вҖңAs surely as you live, \add вүҲyourВҰ134474 majesty\add*,вҖқ \add вүҲreplied\add* AbnerВҰ134460, вҖңI don't knowВҰ134478.вҖқ
\p
\v 56 вҖңFind out whose son he is,вҖқ the kingВҰ134481 \add вүҲhad commanded\add*.
\p
\v 57 ThenВҰ134505 when DavidВҰ134493 had returnedВҰ134492 from \add вүҲkillingВҰ134494\add* the PhilistineВҰ134497, AbnerВҰ134500 broughtВҰ134501 him \add вүҲto stand in frontВҰ134502\add* of Sha'ulВҰ134503, and he was holding \add @Goliat's\add* headВҰ134504.
\v 58 вҖңWhose son are youВҰ134514, lad?вҖқ Sha'ulВҰ134510 \add asked\add*.
\p вҖңI'm the son of yourВҰ134520 servantВҰ134520 YishayВҰ134521, \add вүҲwho lives in Bethlehem\add*,вҖқ \add вүҲreplied\add* DavidВҰ134517.
\c 18
\s1 David's friendship with Yonatan
\rem /s1 Saul Becomes Jealous of David; Jonathan's Covenant with David; Saul's Jealousy of David
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 After \add @David\add* had finishedВҰ134526 speakingВҰ134527 to \add *the king\add*, him andВҰ134525 Yonatan \add вүҲbecame close friends\add*, inВҰ134534 fact Yonatan \add вүҲreally\add* lovedВҰ134536 him.
\v 2 \add From\add* that dayВҰ134543, Sha'ulВҰ134542 kept David \add with him\add*, andВҰ134541 \add вүҲwouldn't allow him to returnВҰ134547 home\add*.
\v 3 ThenВҰ134551 Yonatan andВҰ134551 DavidВҰ134553 \add вүҲmade an agreement together\add*, becauseВҰ134555 \add @Yonatan\add* loved him as much as he loved himself.
\v 4 YonatanВҰ134560 took off the cloak thatВҰ134564 he was wearing and gaveВҰ134566 it to DavidВҰ134567, along with his armourВҰ134568, his swordВҰ134571 and bow, and even his beltВҰ134577.
\v 5 DavidВҰ134580 wentВҰ134579 \add вүҲonВҰ134581 missions\add* whereverВҰ134582 Sha'ul sentВҰ134583 him and \add always\add* succeeded. Sha'ul \add вүҲput him inВҰ134581 charge of the warriorsВҰ134589\add*, and that pleasedВҰ134591 all the peopleВҰ134595, as well as Sha'ul's servantsВҰ134598.
\s1 Sha'ul becomes envious of David
\rem /s1 Saul Becomes Jealous of David
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 6 When \add вүҲthey'd all\add* come back after killingВҰ134606 the PhilistineВҰ134609, the womenВҰ134611 from the IsraeliВҰ134614 citiesВҰ134614 had come out to meet KingВҰ134621 Sha'ulВҰ134620 with singingВҰ134616 and dancingВҰ134618вҖ”playing tambourinesВҰ134622 and \add вүҲother instrumentsВҰ134624 with great happiness\add*.
\v 7 \add вүҲHowever\add*, as they dancedВҰ134628 they sang,\x + \xo 18:7: \xt 1Sam 21:11; 29:5.\x*
\q1 вҖңSha'ulВҰ134631 has \add вүҲkilled\add* his thousands,
\q1 вүҲandВҰ134626 DavidВҰ134634 his tens of thousands.вҖқ
\m
\v 8 Sha'ulВҰ134638 \add вүҲfound that offensive andВҰ134637 it made him very angry\add*. вҖңThey've attributed tens of thousands to DavidВҰ134646,вҖқ he \add вүҲcomplained\add*, вҖңbutВҰ134637 \add only\add* thousands to me. \add вүҲNext thing he'll end up as king\add*.вҖқ
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ134656\add* from that dayВҰ134663 onwardsВҰ134665, Sha'ulВҰ134657 \add вүҲremained wary of DavidВҰ134662 andВҰ134665 kept an eye on him\add*.
\rem /s1 Saul Tries to Kill David
\p
\v 10 Then the next day, an evil spiritВҰ134671 from GodВҰ134672 rushedВҰ134670 onВҰ134680 Sha'ul and \add even\add* inВҰ134680 the middleВҰ134680 of the houseВҰ134682 he \add started\add* prophesyingВҰ134679. As DavidВҰ134683 was playingВҰ134684 near him (as he did every day), Sha'ul was holding a spearВҰ134689
\v 11 andВҰ134694 he \add suddenly\add* hurledВҰ134694 \add *it\add*, saying, вҖңI'llВҰ134700 \add вүҲpin that David to\add* the wallВҰ134702.вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ134694\add* twice when he did that, David \add вүҲmanaged to eludeВҰ134703 him\add*.
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ134708\add* Sha'ulВҰ134709 \add ended up\add* afraidВҰ134708 of DavidВҰ134711 because YahwehВҰ134715 was with him, butВҰ134708 \add вүҲwas no longer with the king\add*.
\v 13 ThenВҰ134721 Sha'ulВҰ134722 sent him \add вүҲout of the room\add* and appointedВҰ134724 him as the commanderВҰ134726 of a thousandВҰ134728 warriors, \add вүҲso\add* he cameВҰ134730 and wentВҰ134729 in frontВҰ134731 of the peopleВҰ134732.\f + \fr 18:13 \ft It's not entirely clear what the implications of this coming and going were (and similarly at the end of v16). It could easily refer to him returning successfully from military excursions.\f*
\v 14 YahwehВҰ134742 was with DavidВҰ134736 and he was succeedingВҰ134741 in \add вүҲeverything he did\add*.
\v 15 Sha'ulВҰ134746 \add вүҲknew about hisВҰ134753 successesВҰ134750 andВҰ134752 couldn't stand looking at himВҰ134753\add*,
\v 16 \add вүҲbutВҰ134755 all the people of\add* YisraelВҰ134757 and YehudahВҰ134758 loved DavidВҰ134762 because \add вүҲthey observed his comingsВҰ134767 and goingsВҰ134766\add*.
\s1 David wins Mikal as his wife
\rem /s1 David Marries Michal; David Marries Saul's Daughter
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 17 \add One day\add* Sha'ul told DavidВҰ134775, вҖңLook, \add here's\add* my oldest daughterВҰ134777 MerabВҰ134779вҖ”I'll giveВҰ134781 her to you for a wife. \add The only condition is that you\add* \add вүҲbecomeВҰ134786 a powerful warrior\add* for me and fightВҰ134792 Yahweh's battlesВҰ134793.вҖқ (Sha'ul had said \add to himself\add*, вҖң\add вүҲI don'tВҰ134797 need to hurt him physicallyвҖ”I'll let the PhilistinesВҰ134807 do that\add* \add for me\add*.вҖқ)
\v 18 вҖңWho am I,вҖқ DavidВҰ134811 \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңand who are my relatives in my father'sВҰ134820 clan in YisraelВҰ134821, that I should become the king's son-in-law?вҖқ
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲHowever,\add* when it was the timeВҰ134829 for Sha'ulВҰ134836 to give his daughterВҰ134834 MerabВҰ134833 to DavidВҰ134837, she was givenВҰ134839 to AdrielВҰ134840 the MeholathiteВҰ134841 \add вүҲto marry\add*.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲNow\add* Sha'ul's \add other\add* daughterВҰ134846 Mikal lovedВҰ134844 DavidВҰ134851, andВҰ134844 \add when\add* they told \add *the king\add*, \add вүҲhe was pleasedВҰ134854 about it\add*,
\v 21 \add вүҲsaying\add* \add to himself\add*, вҖңI'llВҰ134860 giveВҰ134860 her to him \add вүҲso\add* she can become a trap for him \add вүҲso\add* the PhilistinesВҰ134871 \add вүҲcould be the ones to attack\add* him.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ134858\add* he said a secondВҰ134877 time, вҖңYou'll become a son-in-law of mine today.вҖқ
\v 22 ThenВҰ134882 Sha'ulВҰ134883 commandedВҰ134882 his servants, вҖңTell DavidВҰ134891 privatelyВҰ134892, вҖҳListen, the king is pleased withВҰ134892 you, andВҰ134882 all of us his servants love you. \add вүҲSoВҰ134882\add* now \add we think that you should\add* become the king'sВҰ134904 son-in-law.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲSoВҰ134906\add* theyВҰ134906 told DavidВҰ134910 privatelyВҰ134909, \add вүҲbutВҰ134906\add* \add *he\add* \add вүҲrespondedВҰ134915\add*, вҖң\add вүҲSomething that significant isn't likely to happen\add*. I'm \add вүҲhard up\add* andВҰ134906 \add вүҲwithout much honour\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲWhenВҰ134927\add* Sha'ul'sВҰ134929 servantsВҰ134928 told him what DavidВҰ134935 had said,
\v 25 he \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖң\add вүҲPass this onto\add* David, вҖҳThe king \add вүҲdoesn't want an expensive\add* brideВҰ134948 priceвҖ”only a hundredВҰ134950 Philistine foreskinsВҰ134951 taken from the king's enemiesВҰ134954.вҖҷ вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ134938\add* Sha'ulВҰ134939 was \add still wanting\add* the PhilistinesВҰ134952 \add to be the ones\add* \add вүҲto kill\add* David.
\v 26 \add вүҲNowВҰ134976 when\add* DavidВҰ134968 \add вүҲheard this from\add* the servantsВҰ134967, \add вүҲhe decided that he could indeed marry the king'sВҰ134978 daughter within the timeВҰ134981 period that had been given\add*,
\v 27 \add вүҲso\add* he and his men \add вүҲgot ready\add* and went and \add вүҲkilledВҰ134989\add* \em two\em* hundredВҰ134991 Philistine men. He broughtВҰ134993 them to the kingВҰ134999 and \add вүҲhad them counted to fulfill the pledge\add*, and so Sha'ulВҰ135005 \add had to\add* give his daughterВҰ135009 Mikal to becomeВҰ135000 his wife.
\p
\v 28 \add вүҲButВҰ135013 when\add* Sha'ulВҰ135014 \add вүҲrealisedВҰ135013\add* that YahwehВҰ135017 was \add вүҲhelping\add* DavidВҰ135020, and that his daughterВҰ135022 lovedВҰ135025 himВҰ135025,
\v 29 \add вүҲhe became more\add* afraidВҰ135029 of David, \add вүҲso he remained hostile\add* to David \add вүҲfrom thenВҰ135027 on\add*.
\p
\v 30 \add вүҲWhenever\add* the Philistine commanders \add вүҲdecided to attack\add*, DavidВҰ135052 was more successfulВҰ135051 than \add вүҲany other of Sha'ul's commanders, so he became very famous\add*.
\c 19
\s1 Sha'ul persecutes David
\rem /s1 Saul Tries to Kill David; Jonathan Intercedes for David; David Is Persecuted by Saul
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 Then Sha'ulВҰ135062 \add вүҲurged\add* his son Yonatan and all his servantsВҰ135071 to \add вүҲkillВҰ135072\add* David, \add вүҲbutВҰ135061\add* Yonatan \add вүҲreally liked\add* David
\v 2 and told \add *him\add*, вҖңMy fatherВҰ135090 Sha'ulВҰ135089 \add вүҲwants to get rid of youВҰ135091, so pleaseВҰ135095 watch out\add* inВҰ135096 the morningВҰ135096. \add вүҲFind a hiding placeВҰ135098 and stayВҰ135097 there\add*.
\v 3 And \add вүҲwhat I'll do\add*, I'll go out and standВҰ135103 by my father inВҰ135113 the countrysideВҰ135107 whereВҰ135108 you'reВҰ135109 \add hiding\add*, and I'll \add вүҲbring you into the conversation to see what he'll say about you\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSo\add* \add the next morning,\add* Yonatan spokeВҰ135123 well of David to his fatherВҰ135130 Sha'ulВҰ135129, saying, вҖңDon't let the kingВҰ135136 sinВҰ135135 against his servantВҰ135137, against David, becauseВҰ135143 he hasn't sinnedВҰ135141 against you, and actually, \add вүҲhe's been a big help\add* to you.
\v 5 HeВҰ135158 \add вүҲtook his lifeВҰ135153 into his hands when he fought against\add* \add @Goliat\add*, andВҰ135150 YahwehВҰ135160 \add вүҲused it to save\add* all YisraelВҰ135165. \add вүҲSoВҰ135150\add* why would you sinВҰ135169 against innocentВҰ135171 bloodВҰ135170 by putting DavidВҰ135175 to death \add вүҲfor no reason\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 Sha'ulВҰ135179 listenedВҰ135178 to Yonatan, thenВҰ135178 \add *he\add* promised, вҖңAs surely as YahwehВҰ135186 lives, he won't be put to deathВҰ135189.вҖқ
\v 7 \add Afterwards,\add* Yonatan calledВҰ135191 David and told him \add вүҲwhat had been said\add*. ThenВҰ135191 he broughtВҰ135203 David back \add to work for\add* Sha'ulВҰ135210 and \add вүҲthings carried on as beforeВҰ135212\add*.
\rem /s1 Michal Helps David Escape from Saul
\p
\v 8 Then war \add вүҲbroke out\add* again, and DavidВҰ135221 wentВҰ135220 out and battled against the PhilistinesВҰ135223 and defeatedВҰ135224 them \add вүҲso badly that\add* theyВҰ135228 fled away from \add вүҲhimВҰ135229\add*.
\p
\v 9 \add One day\add* as Sha'ulВҰ135238 was sittingВҰ135241 in his houseВҰ135240, an evil spiritВҰ135232 from YahwehВҰ135233 \add вүҲcame onВҰ135240 him\add*. He had his spearВҰ135242 in his hand, andВҰ135231 DavidВҰ135244 was playingВҰ135245 \add the harp\add*.
\v 10 Sha'ulВҰ135249 tried to hit David withВҰ135251 the spear, butВҰ135248 David eludedВҰ135254 him and the spear went into the wall. ThenВҰ135248 David slipped away and fled that nightВҰ135265.
\rem /s1 Michal Saves David's Life
\p
\v 11 Sha'ulВҰ135270 sentВҰ135269 messengersВҰ135271 to watchВҰ135276 David'sВҰ135275 houseВҰ135274 to \add вүҲkillВҰ135277\add* him inВҰ135278 the morningВҰ135278, butВҰ135269 his wife Mikal told \add *him\add*, вҖңIf you don'tВҰ135286 \add do something to\add* save your lifeВҰ135290 tonight, you'll be dead by tomorrowВҰ135292.вҖқ\x + \xo 19:11: \xt Psa 59 header.\x*
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ135296\add* MikalВҰ135297 loweredВҰ135296 DavidВҰ135300 out throughВҰ135301 the windowВҰ135302, and he was able to slip out and take off.
\v 13 ThenВҰ135307 \add *she\add* tookВҰ135307 a household idolВҰ135311 and put it inВҰ135322 the bed, putting a goats' hairВҰ135318 quiltВҰ135317 \add вүҲwhere the headВҰ135320 should be\add* and coveringВҰ135321 it withВҰ135322 the \add bed-\add*clothes.
\v 14 \add вүҲWhen\add* Sha'ulВҰ135326 sentВҰ135325 messengersВҰ135327 to \add вүҲarrest\add* DavidВҰ135331, she \add вүҲtold\add* \add <them\add*, вҖңHe's sickВҰ135333.вҖқ
\v 15 Sha'ulВҰ135338 sentВҰ135337 the messengersВҰ135341 \add back\add*, \add вүҲtelling\add* \add <them\add*, вҖңBring him up to me \add вүҲbed and all so I can killВҰ135351 him\add*.вҖқ
\v 16 \add вүҲButВҰ135353\add* when the messengersВҰ135354 \add вүҲreturned\add*, look, it was a household idolВҰ135356 in the bed with a goats' hairВҰ135361 quiltВҰ135360 as itsВҰ135362 headВҰ135362.
\v 17 Sha'ul \add had Mikal brought in and\add* \add вүҲquestioned\add*, вҖңWhy did you deceiveВҰ135371 me like that and sent my enemyВҰ135375 off, so that he slipped away?вҖқ
\p вҖңHe \add вүҲtold me that he'd killВҰ135388 me\add*,вҖқ MichalВҰ135368 \add вүҲanswered\add* Sha'ul, вҖң\add вүҲif I didn't help him escapeВҰ135376\add*.вҖқ
\rem /s1 David Joins Samuel in Ramah
\p
\v 18 \add After\add* DavidВҰ135390 had slipped away, he went to ShemuelВҰ135411 in RamahВҰ135397 and told him everything that Sha'ulВҰ135408 had done to him, thenВҰ135390 \add вүҲthe two of them\add* went and stayed in Nayot.
\v 19 \add вүҲButВҰ135416\add* Sha'ulВҰ135417 was told that DavidВҰ135420 was inВҰ135421 NayotВҰ135421 \add вүҲnear\add* RamahВҰ135423,
\v 20 \add вүҲso\add* \add *he\add* sentВҰ135425 messengers to \add вүҲcapture\add* DavidВҰ135431. \add вүҲWhenВҰ135425\add* they sawВҰ135432 a group of prophets prophesying and ShemuelВҰ135438 standingВҰ135439 \add вүҲas head\add* over them, God's spiritВҰ135447 came onto Sha'ul's messengers and they also prophesied.
\v 21 TheyВҰ135464 told Sha'ulВҰ135455 and he sent more messengers and they also prophesied. \add *He\add* sent messengers a thirdВҰ135467 time, and they \add started\add* prophesying as well.
\v 22 \add вүҲFinally\add* Sha'ul \add himself\add* \add вүҲheaded towards\add* Ramah and got as far as the large \add water\add* cisternВҰ135481 in Seku. He askedВҰ135485 \add вүҲaround about\add* ShemuelВҰ135488 and DavidВҰ135489, and \add вүҲwas told thatВҰ135483\add* they were in Nayot \add вүҲnear\add* Ramah.
\v 23 \add вүҲSoВҰ135496\add* he wentВҰ135515 to Nayot, andВҰ135496 God's spiritВҰ135508 came onВҰ135502 him as well. As he \add вүҲwalked\add*, he \add kept\add* prophesyingВҰ135512 untilВҰ135513 he entered Nayot.
\v 24 He took off his \add outer\add* clothesВҰ135524 and prophesied \add вүҲinВҰ135546 frontВҰ135529\add* of Shemuel. He lay \add вүҲundressed\add* all that dayВҰ135535 and all nightВҰ135539, so \add that's why\add* peopleВҰ135543 ask, вҖңIs Sha'ulВҰ135545 a prophet as well?вҖқ\x + \xo 19:24: \xt 1Sam 10:11-12.\x*
\c 20
\s1 Yonatan helps David
\rem /s1 The Friendship of David and Jonathan; Jonathan Helps David
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 Then DavidВҰ135550 fled from Nayot \add вүҲnear\add* RamahВҰ135553 and wentВҰ135554 to Yonatan and \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңWhat have I done? What did I do wrong? What sinВҰ135566 \add вүҲhas made your father so angry\add* that he \add вүҲwants to take\add* my lifeВҰ135573?вҖқ
\p
\v 2 вҖңFar from it,вҖқ Yonatan \add вүҲrespondedВҰ135575\add*. вҖңYou won'tВҰ135578 die. Listen, my father doesn't do \add вүҲanything, big or smallВҰ135590, without telling me\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ135575\add* why would my father hide this from me \add if it was his plan\add*? \add No,\add* \add вүҲyou're wrong\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖңFor sure, your father knowsВҰ135612 that \add вүҲyou've taken a liking to me\add*,вҖқ said David, вҖңand he \add вүҲwould have decided not to tell you so you wouldn't be upset\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ135607 David made an oath againВҰ135608, вҖңIndeed, as YahwehВҰ135632 is alive, and as your soulВҰ135634 is alive, deathВҰ135639 \add вүҲis definitely only a step away from me\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 вҖңI'llВҰ135650 do anything for youвҖ”whateverВҰ135646 you sayВҰ135648,вҖқ Yonatan \add вүҲconfirmed\add*.
\p
\v 5 вҖңListen, the new moonВҰ135662 \add celebration\add* is tomorrowВҰ135663, and \add вүҲI'll definitely be expected to\add* sit withВҰ135674 the kingВҰ135670 to eatВҰ135671,вҖқ DavidВҰ135656 told \add *him\add*. вҖң\add вүҲButВҰ135655\add* you \add shouldВҰ135672\add* let me goВҰ135672, and I'll hideВҰ135673 myselfВҰ135673 inВҰ135674 the countrysideВҰ135674 untilВҰ135675 the thirdВҰ135677 eveningВҰ135676.\x + \xo 20:5: \xt Num 28:11.\x*
\v 6 If your father missesВҰ135682 me, then tell \add <him\add*, вҖҳDavidВҰ135688 \add вүҲbegged me to let him go to his home in\add* Bethlehem, to \add вүҲjoin his clan for their yearly\add* sacrificeВҰ135695.вҖҷ
\v 7 If \add @your father\add* says, вҖҳThat's fine,вҖҷ then your servantВҰ135708 \add вүҲcan relax\add*. \add вүҲButВҰ135709 if he gets reallyВҰ135711 angry\add*, \add вүҲyou'll knowВҰ135714 that he's planning\add* evilВҰ135718.
\v 8 \add If that's the case,\add* \add вүҲit'll be up to you to do what's right withВҰ135727 your servant inВҰ135727 terms of our agreement before\add* YahwehВҰ135728. If \add вүҲI've been disloyal to the king,\add* kill me yourselfвҖ”\add вүҲno need to drag me to him\add*.
\p
\v 9 вҖң\add вүҲDon't even think of it\add*,вҖқ Yonatan \add вүҲrespondedВҰ135751\add*. вҖңIf I find out that my fatherВҰ135766 \add вүҲhas decided to harm\add* you, I'llВҰ135760 \add вүҲcertainly\add* tell you.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 вҖңIf your father \add вүҲdoes have a cruel plan\add*, who'll tell me?вҖқ DavidВҰ135776 \add вүҲasked\add* Yonatan.
\p
\v 11 вҖңCome \add вүҲwith me\add* out to the countryside.вҖқ Yonatan \add вүҲreplied\add*. \add вүҲSo\add* theyВҰ135799 wentВҰ135799 out to the countryside together
\v 12 and \add *he\add* \add вүҲpromised\add* DavidВҰ135808, вҖңBy YahwehВҰ135809 the godВҰ135810 of YisraelВҰ135811, I will definitely soundВҰ135814 out my fatherВҰ135817 around this timeВҰ135818 tomorrowВҰ135820, or \add вүҲsoon after\add*. If \add вүҲit looks\add* goodВҰ135824 for \add *you\add*, then I'llВҰ135814 certainly sendВҰ135831 \add вүҲa message to let you know\add*.
\v 13 \add ButВҰ135843\add* if \add *he's\add* planning evil for you, may Yahweh punish me similarly or even worse if I don't inform you, and send you away so you can leave in peaceВҰ135861. And may Yahweh be with you just like he used to be with my father.
\v 14 \add вүҲButВҰ135871\add* as long as I'm stillВҰ135874 aliveВҰ135875, please \add keep our\add* \add вүҲagreement of faithfulness before\add* YahwehВҰ135881 so I won'tВҰ135871 dieВҰ135883.
\v 15 Don'tВҰ135902 ever \add вүҲterminate\add* that agreement of faithfulness towards my family, even when YahwehВҰ135898 \add вүҲdestroys\add* yourВҰ135890 enemiesВҰ135901 \add вүҲwherever they are\add*.\x + \xo 20:15: \xt 2Sam 9:1.\x*
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ135908\add* Yonatan made a \add вүҲmulti-generational\add* agreement with David, \add adding\add*, вҖңAnd may YahwehВҰ135915 \add вүҲpunish David'sВҰ135913 enemiesВҰ135917\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ135920 YonatanВҰ135921 got DavidВҰ135925 to promise againВҰ135920 becauseВҰ135926 he loved him as much as he loved his \add вүҲown lifeВҰ135931\add*,
\v 18 and \add *he\add* told him, вҖңTheВҰ135938 new moonВҰ135940 \add celebration\add* is tomorrowВҰ135939, and you'll be missedВҰ135941 because yourВҰ135944 seatВҰ135944 will be emptyВҰ135943.
\v 19 TheВҰ135962 following dayВҰ135957, goВҰ135949 to the placeВҰ135952 whereВҰ135953 you hid \add вүҲbefore\add* andВҰ135946 stayВҰ135959 by the \add вүҲbig\add* rockВҰ135961.
\v 20 I'llВҰ135968 shootВҰ135968 threeВҰ135965 arrowsВҰ135966 to the side of itВҰ135967, as if \add вүҲtrying to hit\add* a targetВҰ135972.
\v 21 ThenВҰ135974 I'llВҰ135975 sendВҰ135975 \add &my\add* boy to find the arrows. If I tell \add *him\add* that they're on my side, thenВҰ135974 just as YahwehВҰ136005 lives \add вүҲit'll be safe for\add* youВҰ135992 to comeВҰ135996 \add out\add*.
\v 22 \add вүҲButВҰ136007\add* if IВҰ136010 tell the boy that they're on the far side, goВҰ136016 because YahwehВҰ136019 is sending you away.
\v 23 AsВҰ136024 for \add вүҲour pact\add*, YahwehВҰ136027 \add вүҲwill watch over us andВҰ136021 our descendants\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲSo\add* DavidВҰ136036 hid himselfВҰ136035 in the countrysideВҰ136037, and \add at\add* the new moonВҰ136039 \add celebrations\add*, the kingВҰ136041 satВҰ136040 down to eatВҰ136046вҖ”
\v 25 sitting atВҰ136055 his \add вүҲusual\add* seat by the wallВҰ136059. Yonatan \add вүҲsat opposite\add*, andВҰ136048 AbnerВҰ136063 sat beside Sha'ulВҰ136065. \add вүҲNo one was sitting inВҰ136055 David'sВҰ136068 seat\add*
\v 26 \add вүҲbutВҰ136070\add* Sha'ulВҰ136073 didn'tВҰ136070 say anythingВҰ136074 that dayВҰ136075, \add вүҲthinking\add*, вҖң\add вүҲSomething must have happened that made him\add* \add ceremonially\add* unclean.вҖқ
\v 27 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the next day of the \add вүҲcelebration\add* when DavidВҰ136096 was still missing, Sha'ulВҰ136099 asked his son Yonatan, вҖңWhy didn'tВҰ136105 Yishay'sВҰ136110 son come to the meal yesterdayВҰ136113 or today?вҖқ
\p
\v 28 вҖңDavidВҰ136128 \add вүҲbegged\add* me \add вүҲto let him go to\add* Bethlehem,вҖқ Yonatan answeredВҰ136121.
\v 29 вҖңHe \add вүҲrequested\add*, вҖҳPlease \add вүҲrelease me\add* because our clan's sacrificeВҰ136139 will be in the cityВҰ136142, and my brother has \add вүҲtoldВҰ136144 me to be thereВҰ136160\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ136135\add* now, if I'veВҰ136151 foundВҰ136151 favourВҰ136152 in your eyesВҰ136153, please let me slip away and \add вүҲgoВҰ136136 to\add* seeВҰ136156 my brothersВҰ136159.вҖҷ \add вүҲThat's why\add* he hasn't comeВҰ136165 to the king'sВҰ136169 tableВҰ136168.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 Sha'ulВҰ136175 \add вүҲwas furious at\add* Yonatan and \add вүҲyelled at\add* him, вҖң\add You\add* son of a perverseВҰ136181, rebelliousВҰ136182 woman! Do \add you think that\add* I don'tВҰ136183 know that you're \add вүҲtaking the side of\add* Yishay'sВҰ136191 son? It's to your \add вүҲdetriment\add* and to the shame of your mother'sВҰ136195 nakednessВҰ136194,
\v 31 because as long as thatВҰ136201 son of YishayВҰ136204 stays alive on this earth, you and your kingdomВҰ136212 will never be establishedВҰ136210. NowВҰ136216, sendВҰ136214 \add men\add* and \add вүҲarrest\add* him, because he's \add вүҲon his way to the grave\add*!вҖқ
\p
\v 32 вҖңWhy should he be put to deathВҰ136234?вҖқ Yonatan \add вүҲretorted\add*. вҖңWhat \add wrong\add* has he done?вҖқ
\p
\v 33 ThenВҰ136238 Sha'ulВҰ136239 hurledВҰ136238 his spearВҰ136242 at him to \add вүҲkill him\add*, andВҰ136238 YonatanВҰ136246 knew \add thenВҰ136238\add* that his fatherВҰ136252 had \add already\add* \add вүҲdeterminedВҰ136249 to kill\add* DavidВҰ136256.
\v 34 Yonatan angrily got up from the tableВҰ136262. He didn'tВҰ136266 eat any food that secondВҰ136272 dayВҰ136269 of the \add вүҲcelebration\add*вҖ”he was upset about David because his fatherВҰ136281 had dishonoured him.\f + \fr 20:34 \ft It's not entirely clear who this вҖҳhimвҖҷ was (as Sha'ul had seriously dishonoured Yonatan as well), so we've left it ambiguous (although David was certainly the last name mentioned).\f*
\v 35 \add вүҲSo it was that the following\add* morningВҰ136285, Yonatan wentВҰ136286 out to the countrysideВҰ136288 \add вүҲatВҰ136285 the timeВҰ136289 agreed\add* with DavidВҰ136290, taking a smallВҰ136292 boyВҰ136291 \add with him\add*.
\v 36 вҖңRun \add ahead\add*вҖ”find the arrows thatВҰ136303 I'm aboutВҰ136305 to shootВҰ136305,вҖқ he told his boy. The boy ranВҰ136307 andВҰ136295 he shot the arrow to \add вүҲgo over his head\add*.
\v 37 The boy wentВҰ136314 to where the arrow was, \add вүҲbutВҰ136314\add* Yonatan calledВҰ136323 out, вҖңIsn't the arrow \add вүҲfurther past\add* youВҰ136330?вҖқ
\v 38 ThenВҰ136333 he \add вүҲadded\add*, вҖң\add вүҲHurry up! Don't mess around\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ136333\add* the boyВҰ136336 pickedВҰ136342 up the arrowВҰ136347 andВҰ136333 brought it back to his masterВҰ136352,
\v 39 \add вүҲbutВҰ136354\add* the boyВҰ136354 didn'tВҰ136355 \add вүҲrealise what had just happened\add*вҖ”only YonatanВҰ136360 andВҰ136354 DavidВҰ136361 knew.
\v 40 ThenВҰ136367 YonatanВҰ136368 gaveВҰ136367 his equipment to the boyВҰ136374 andВҰ136378 \add вүҲsent him back to\add* the cityВҰ136382.
\p
\v 41 \add When\add* the boyВҰ136384 \add вүҲwas gone\add*, David came up from the side and \add вүҲdropped onto his knees\add*, bowing threeВҰ136394 timesВҰ136395 with his faceВҰ136391 to the ground. Then they \add вүҲgreeted each other with a kiss and cried together, although David cried the most\add*.
\v 42 Then Yonatan told David, вҖңGo in peaceВҰ136416, because us twoВҰ136419 have \add вүҲmade a pact together\add* in Yahweh's nameВҰ136421, \add вүҲagreeing\add*, вҖҳYahweh \add will watch\add* between me and youВҰ136428, and between my descendants and your descendants forever.вҖҷ вҖқ Then \add @David\add* set off and Yonatan \add вүҲwent back\add* to the city.
\c 21
\s1 David stays at Nob
\rem /s1 David Flees from Saul; David Runs from Saul; David at Nob; David and the Holy Bread
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 David \add вүҲwentВҰ136442\add* to the priest Ahimelek at Nob, \add вүҲbutВҰ136439\add* Ahimelek trembled \add вүҲwhen he saw\add* David and \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңWhy are you \add here\add* by yourself? \add вүҲHow come you don't have a companion\add*?вҖқ\x + \xo 21:1-6: \xt Mat 12:3-4; Mrk 2:25-26; Luk 6:3.\x*
\p
\v 2 вҖңThe king \add вүҲsent me on an errand\add*,вҖқ DavidВҰ136447 \add вүҲreplied\add*, вҖң\add вүҲbutВҰ136446\add* he told me \add вүҲnot to tell anyoneВҰ136462 about the matter that he sent me on\add*. \add вүҲPlus\add* I've \add вүҲtold my young men where to meet me\add*.
\v 3 \add вүҲNow, what food do you have on\add* hand? Give me five loaves of bread or whatever you can find.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 вҖңThere is no ordinary bread \add вүҲonВҰ136512\add* hand,вҖқ the priest answered. вҖңButВҰ136501 thereВҰ136504 is the sacred bread, if only the young men have kept themselves from women.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҖң\add вүҲThere's definitely been no womenВҰ136543 near us for\add* three days,вҖқ DavidВҰ136521 told the priestВҰ136518. вҖң\add вүҲThat's how I always do missions\add*. The men\f + \fr 21:5 \ft The Hebrew says вҖҳthe men's vesselsвҖҷ (or вҖҳcontainersвҖҷ). It's not culturally clear if that referred to their вҖҳbodiesвҖҷ (as this translation implies) or to something they carried.\f* have been pure, even though it was a common journey, and today \add вүҲeven more so\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲSo\add* the priestВҰ136551 gave him the sacredВҰ136575 bread, because there was no other bread there other than the \add previous day's\add* bread of the presence which had been removed from \add вүҲinВҰ136563 front\add* of Yahweh to be replaced by fresh bread.\x + \xo 21:6: \xt Lev 24:5-9.\x*
\p
\v 7 \add Now it so happened\add* that one of Sha'ul's servants was thereВҰ136588 that dayВҰ136602 \add вүҲpresentingВҰ136595 himself to\add* YahwehВҰ136598. He was Doeg the Edomite, a \add вүҲleader\add* of Sha'ul's herdsmen.
\p
\v 8 David \add вүҲasked\add* Ahimelek, вҖң\add вүҲDo you have\add* any spear or sword here? \add вүҲI didn't have time to grab my sword or my weapons when I left\add*, because the king's matter was urgent.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖң\add I've only got\add* Goliat's sword,вҖқ \add вүҲreplied\add* the priest. вҖң\add From\add* the Philistine who you \add вүҲkilled\add* in the Elah valley. Look, it's wrapped in the cloak behind the sacred apron. If you want to take it for yourself, take \add <it\add*, because there's no other \add вүҲsword around\add* here.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* there's no \add вүҲother sword\add* like it,вҖқ said DavidВҰ136625. вҖң\add вүҲGet it for\add* me.вҖқ\x + \xo 21:9: \xt 1Sam 17:51.\x*
\s1 David flees to Gat
\rem /s1 David Flees to Gath; David at Gath
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 10 Then DavidВҰ136690 left and \add continuedВҰ136659\add* \add вүҲmoving to distance himself\add* from Sha'ul, and he went to King Akish of Gat.
\v 11 \add вүҲButВҰ136697\add* Akish's servants \add вүҲcomplained\add* to him, вҖңIsn't that David \add who'll become\add* kingВҰ136709 of \add вүҲIsrael\add*? \add вүҲIsn't he the one they sing about when they dance, chanting\add*, вҖҳSha'ulВҰ136704 has \add вүҲkilled\add* his thousands, and David his tens of thousands?вҖҷ вҖқ\x + \xo 21:11: \xt 1Sam 18:7; 29:5.\x*
\p
\v 12 DavidВҰ136720 \add вүҲlistened to those words without any reaction because\add* he was very afraid of \add what\add* KingВҰ136721 Akish \add might do\add*,\x + \xo 21:12: \xt Psa 56 header.\x*
\v 13 \add вүҲso\add* he changed his behaviour \add вүҲwhen he was withВҰ136743 them\add* and pretended to be insane. He \add вүҲscratched\add* onВҰ136743 \add wooden\add* doors and let his saliva \add вүҲdribble\add* down his beard.\x + \xo 21:13: \xt Psa 34 header.\x*
\v 14 Then \add King\add* Akish \add вүҲcomplained\add* to his servants, вҖңLook, \add вүҲthat man's\add* insane. Why did you all bring him to me?
\v 15 \add вүҲDon't I already have enough madmen around hereвҖ”why add another? Must that man come\add* into my house?вҖқ
\c 22
\s1 David moves around but gains followers
\rem /s1 David as outlaw captain; The Slaughter of the Priests; David at Adullam and Mizpah; David and His Followers at Adullam; David at the Cave of Adullam
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲSo\add* DavidВҰ136807 left there and slipped away to the cave at AdullamВҰ136813. \add вүҲWhen his brothersВҰ136815 and other relatives found out\add*, they went and \add joined\add* him there.\x + \xo 22:1: \xt Psa 57 header; Psa 142 header.\x*
\v 2 \add Over time,\add* any man \add вүҲwho was in trouble\add*, or \add вүҲin debt\add*, or \add вүҲdiscontented\add* gatheredВҰ136824 \add вүҲaround\add* him, andВҰ136824 he became \add вүҲtheir leader\add*вҖ”some four hundredВҰ136849 men \add in all\add*.
\p
\v 3 From thereВҰ136854, DavidВҰ136853 wentВҰ136852 to Mitspah in Moab, andВҰ136852 he \add вүҲasked\add* the kingВҰ136861 of Moab, вҖңPlease let my \add вүҲparents\add* \add вүҲstay here in the palace\add* with you untilВҰ136869 \add вүҲI find out\add* what GodВҰ136877 will do for me.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ136879\add* he \add вүҲtook them to\add* the kingВҰ136883 \add вүҲwhere\add* they stayed withВҰ136893 him \add вүҲthe entireВҰ136887 timeВҰ136889 that DavidВҰ136892 livedВҰ136885\add* inВҰ136893 the fortress.
\p
\v 5 Then the prophetВҰ136898 GadВҰ136897 told David, вҖңDon't stay in the fortress. \add вүҲLeave it\add* and come back to \add вүҲYehudah'sВҰ136910 regionВҰ136909\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* David left and wentВҰ136911 to the HeretВҰ136915 forestВҰ136914 \add in Yehudah\add*.
\s1 The slaughter of the priests
\rem /s1 Saul Kills the Priests of Nob; Saul Slaughters the Priests at Nob
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 6 \add OneВҰ136926 day,\add* Sha'ulВҰ136919 was sittingВҰ136927 holding his spearВҰ136933 underneathВҰ136929 the tamariskВҰ136931 treeВҰ136931 onВҰ136928 a hill \add near\add* GibeahВҰ136928 withВҰ136928 all his servantsВҰ136937 stationed \add вүҲaround\add* him, \add вүҲwhen\add* \add *he\add* heard \add вүҲwhere\add* DavidВҰ136922 and his menВҰ136923 were,
\v 7 and he \add вүҲaccused\add* his servantsВҰ136943, вҖңListen now, you Benyamites. Will Yishay'sВҰ136957 son also\f + \fr 22:7 \ft See note on вҖҳЧқЦ·Ч’вҖҷ (вҖҳgamвҖҷ) at https://www.sil.org/resources/publications/entry/99313.\f* giveВҰ136954 fieldsВҰ136958 and vineyardsВҰ136959 to all of you? Will he make all of you commanders of thousandsВҰ136963 and commanders of hundredsВҰ136965?
\v 8 \add Yes,\add* all of you have conspiredВҰ136968 against me. \add вүҲNot one of you informed me when\add* my \add own\add* son made a \add вүҲpact\add* withВҰ136977 \add that\add* son of YishayВҰ136984. And noneВҰ136985 of you \add вүҲtook my side or even informed me\add* that my son has \add вүҲencouraged\add* my servantВҰ136999 to lie inВҰ136977 ambushВҰ137001 against me as he is today!вҖқ
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲNow\add* DoegВҰ137007 the Edomite was stationed there with Sha'ul's servantsВҰ137013, and he \add spoke up\add*, вҖңI sawВҰ137017 Yishay'sВҰ137022 son go to NobВҰ137024 and talk with Ahimelek the priest,\x + \xo 22:9-10: \xt 1Sam 21:7-9; Psa 52 header.\x*
\v 10 and \add @the priest\add* \add вүҲasked YahwehВҰ137035 for directions\add* for him, and gave him food and Goliat'sВҰ137041 swordВҰ137040.вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Slaughter of the Priests
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ137046 the king \add вүҲsummoned\add* Ahitub'sВҰ137054 son AhimelekВҰ137051 and all his relatives who were priestsВҰ137055 to NobВҰ137063, and they all came to the king.
\v 12 вҖңListen now, son of AhitubВҰ137078,вҖқ said Sha'ulВҰ137072.
\p вҖң\add вүҲGo ahead\add* my masterВҰ137081,вҖқ \add вүҲanswered\add* Ahimelek.
\p
\v 13 вҖңWhy have you all conspiredВҰ137088 against me?вҖқ asked Sha'ulВҰ137086. вҖңYou gaveВҰ137094 breadВҰ137097 to Yishay'sВҰ137093 son, and a swordВҰ137098, and you \add вүҲasked guidance from\add* GodВҰ137101 for himВҰ137084, \add so now\add* he's risen up against meвҖ”lying inВҰ137094 ambushВҰ137104 this very dayВҰ137105?вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖң\add вүҲIsn't DavidВҰ137119 one of your most\add* faithfulВҰ137120 servantsВҰ137118?вҖқ Ahimelek answeredВҰ137109 the king. вҖңHe's the king's son-in-law and commander over your guards, and isn't he honouredВҰ137127 in your houseВҰ137128?
\v 15 Did I beginВҰ137131 to inquireВҰ137132 for him from GodВҰ137136 today? Far be it from me! Don't let the kingВҰ137142 \add вүҲaccuse\add* his servant or any of my father'sВҰ137148 householdВҰ137147, because your servant doesn't know about any of thisвҖ”\add вүҲnothing atВҰ137136 all\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңFor certain, Ahimelek,вҖқ the kingВҰ137163 \add вүҲdeclared\add*. вҖңyou andВҰ137162 all your father's householdВҰ137170 will certainly die \add for that\add*!вҖқ
\v 17 ThenВҰ137173 the king \add вүҲcommanded\add* his messengers who were stationed beside him, вҖңTurn around andВҰ137173 put Yahweh's priests to deathВҰ137179 because \add вүҲthey've taken David'sВҰ137189 side\add*. And because they knew he was fleeingВҰ137194, butВҰ137173 they didn'tВҰ137196 \add вүҲinform me\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ137173\add* the king's servantsВҰ137205 weren't willingВҰ137204 to attackВҰ137211 Yahweh's priests.
\v 18 \add вүҲSo\add* the kingВҰ137217 \add вүҲcommanded\add* Doeg the Edomite, вҖңYou turn around and attack the priests.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* Doeg turnedВҰ137224 and he himself attacked the priests. He \add вүҲkilledВҰ137232\add* eighty-five men that dayВҰ137234 who \add вүҲwore\add* sacred linenВҰ137241 aprons.
\v 19 \add вүҲAlso\add* \add at\add* NobВҰ137244 (the cityВҰ137245 of priestsВҰ137247) he \add вүҲkilled\add* men and women \add вүҲwith his\add* sword, childrenВҰ137256 and infants, cattle, donkeysВҰ137261, and sheepВҰ137262.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲButВҰ137267\add* one of Ahimelek's sons \add вүҲwas able to slip away\add*. His nameВҰ137275 was Evyatar andВҰ137267 he fled \add to join\add* DavidВҰ137279,
\v 21 andВҰ137281 \add вүҲinformed\add* \add *him\add* that Sha'ulВҰ137286 had \add commanded Doeg to\add* kill Yahweh's priestsВҰ137288.
\v 22 вҖңI knewВҰ137294 on that dayВҰ137295,вҖқ DavidВҰ137292 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ137291\add*, вҖңwhen DoegВҰ137300 the Edomite was thereВҰ137299, that he would \add вүҲprobably\add* tell Sha'ulВҰ137307. \add вүҲIt's my fault that your father andВҰ137291 all his family were murdered\add*.
\v 23 Stick with meвҖ”don'tВҰ137318 be afraidВҰ137320, because \add вүҲthe one who wants to kill me would kill youВҰ137335 as well\add*. You'll be safe with me.вҖқ
\c 23
