\p
\v 1 \add Some time later,\add* DavidВҰ137339 was told, вҖңListen, the PhilistinesВҰ137342 are fightingВҰ137343 againstВҰ137344 \add the city of\add* Ke'ilah andВҰ137345 theyВҰ137345 are \add вүҲstealing grain from\add* the threshingВҰ137349 floorsВҰ137349,вҖқ
\v 2 \add вүҲso\add* he asked Yahweh, вҖңShould I go and attack those PhilistinesВҰ137357?вҖқ
\p вҖңGo and attack the Philistines and save Ke'ilah,вҖқ Yahweh \add вүҲrespondedВҰ137360\add*.
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲButВҰ137373\add* David'sВҰ137375 menВҰ137374 \add вүҲwarned\add* him, вҖңListen, we're afraid here inВҰ137380 YehudahВҰ137380, andВҰ137373 \add вүҲwe'd be even more afraid\add* if we went to Ke'ilah againstВҰ137387 the Philistines' \add battleВҰ137389\add* linesВҰ137389.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSo\add* DavidВҰ137395 \add вүҲdouble-checked\add* withВҰ137397 YahwehВҰ137400 \add *who\add* answeredВҰ137399, вҖң\add вүҲGet ready\add* \add and\add* goВҰ137403 to Ke'ilah, because I'm aboutВҰ137408 to giveВҰ137408 \add вүҲyou victory over\add* the PhilistinesВҰ137411.вҖқ
\v 5 ThenВҰ137414 DavidВҰ137415 and his menВҰ137416 wentВҰ137414 to Ke'ilah and battled againstВҰ137420 the PhilistinesВҰ137420вҖ”\add вүҲthoroughly defeatingВҰ137427\add* them and taking theirВҰ137424 livestockВҰ137424, \add вүҲthus\add* saving the inhabitantsВҰ137432 of Ke'ilah.
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲNow\add* when Ahimelek's son Evyatar had fled to DavidВҰ137444 atВҰ137437 Ke'ilah, he'd \add вүҲbrought\add* a sacred apron \add вүҲwithВҰ137437 him\add*.
