\p
\v 7 Sha'ulВҰ137451 was told that DavidВҰ137455 had gone to Ke'ilah, \add вүҲso\add* he saidВҰ137457, вҖң\add Ah,\add* GodВҰ137461 has \add вүҲdeserted him andВҰ137450 given him to me\add* because he's shut himselfВҰ137464 inВҰ137462 by \add вүҲgoingВҰ137465\add* into a \add walled\add* cityВҰ137466 withВҰ137462 doorsВҰ137467 \add вүҲthat can be barred shut\add*.вҖқ
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ137470\add* Sha'ulВҰ137471 \add вүҲinitiated preparations\add* to goВҰ137478 to Ke'ilahВҰ137479 to entrap DavidВҰ137483 andВҰ137484 his menВҰ137486.
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲButВҰ137488\add* DavidВҰ137489 \add вүҲdiscovered\add* that Sha'ulВҰ137492 was \add вүҲplanning to destroy\add* him, \add вүҲso\add* he \add вүҲsummoned\add* Evyatar the priestВҰ137499, вҖңBring the sacred apron here.вҖқ
\v 10 Then DavidВҰ137505 \add вүҲprayed\add*, вҖңYahwehВҰ137506, GodВҰ137507 of YisraelВҰ137508, yourВҰ137511 servantВҰ137511 has heardВҰ137510 that Sha'ulВҰ137515 is \add вүҲintending\add* to comeВҰ137516 to Ke'ilahвҖ”to destroyВҰ137520 the cityВҰ137521 becauseВҰ137522 of me.
\v 11 Will Sha'ulВҰ137529 come \add вүҲhere\add*, just as your servant has heardВҰ137531? Will the masters of Ke'ilah \add вүҲturn me over to him\add*? Yahweh, GodВҰ137534 of YisraelВҰ137535, pleaseВҰ137538 tell your servant.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* he will \add вүҲgo there\add*,вҖқ Yahweh \add вүҲanswered\add*.
\p
\v 12 вҖң\add And\add* will the masters of Ke'ilah \add вүҲhandВҰ137554\add* me andВҰ137545 my menВҰ137553 \add вүҲover to\add* Sha'ulВҰ137556?вҖқ DavidВҰ137546 \add вүҲasked\add* \add again\add*.
\p And YahwehВҰ137558 said, вҖңThey will deliverВҰ137559 up.вҖқ
\rem /s1 David Hides in the Wilderness
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲSo\add* David and his menВҰ137564 (about 600 \add вүҲof them\add*), \add вүҲleft\add* Ke'ilah and \add вүҲmoved around from place to place\add*. \add вүҲWhen\add* Sha'ulВҰ137574 was told that David had slipped away from Ke'ilah, heВҰ137578 \add вүҲdidn't continue withВҰ137572 his plans\add*.
\s1 Sha'ul pursues David
