\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 14 DavidВҰ137585 stayed in \add various\add* strongholdsВҰ137587 in the wilderness, andВҰ137584 \add sometimes\add* he stayed in the hill countryВҰ137589 in the ZifВҰ137592 wilderness. Sha'ulВҰ137594 \add вүҲkept searching for them\add*, butВҰ137584 GodВҰ137601 didn'tВҰ137598 \add вүҲallow him to capture them\add*.
\rem /s1 David Eludes Saul in the Wilderness
\v 15 \add Once\add* DavidВҰ137605 was \add staying\add* inВҰ137616 the ZifВҰ137618 wildernessВҰ137616 andВҰ137615 heВҰ137609 sawВҰ137604 that Sha'ulВҰ137610 had \add вүҲarrived there to try to kill him\add*.
\v 16 Then Sha'ul's son Yonatan wentВҰ137627 to DavidВҰ137630 atВҰ137636 HoreshВҰ137631 and \add вүҲencouragedВҰ137632 him to keep trusting\add* GodВҰ137636,
\v 17 saying, вҖңDon't be afraidВҰ137642, because my father Sha'ulВҰ137647 won'tВҰ137640 \add вүҲcapture\add* you. As for you, you'll reignВҰ137650 over YisraelВҰ137653, andВҰ137638 I'llВҰ137655 be \add вүҲyour secondВҰ137658 in command\add*. Even my father knows \add вүҲthat\add*.вҖқ
\v 18 \add Again,\add* the two of them \add вүҲmade an agreement\add* before YahwehВҰ137670. ThenВҰ137666 DavidВҰ137672 stayed atВҰ137673 HoreshВҰ137673 andВҰ137666 Yonatan returned homeВҰ137676.\x + \xo 23:18: \xt 1Sam 18:3.\x*
\p
\v 19 \add Some men\add* \add вүҲfrom Zif\add* wentВҰ137679 to Sha'ulВҰ137683 atВҰ137690 GibeahВҰ137684, saying, вҖң\add вүҲWe're pretty sure thatВҰ137694\add* David'sВҰ137687 hidingВҰ137688 himselfВҰ137688 amongВҰ137689 us in the strongholdsВҰ137690 in HoreshВҰ137691, onВҰ137690 the HakilahВҰ137693 hill southВҰ137695 of YeshimonВҰ137696.\x + \xo 23:19: \xt Psa 54 header.\x*
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ137698\add* now, \add вүҲyour majesty\add*, come \add вүҲover whenever you want\add*, andВҰ137698 \add вүҲwe'll make sure he's handed over to you\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 вҖңMay you all be blessedВҰ137713 by YahwehВҰ137715,вҖқ Sha'ulВҰ137712 respondedВҰ137711, вҖңbecause you've had compassionВҰ137717 on me.
\v 22 Please go back and \add вүҲdouble-check\add* and \add find out\add* who's seenВҰ137734 himВҰ137734 thereВҰ137735. \add вүҲLearn more\add* and \add вүҲlook at the placeВҰ137729 yourselves\add*, because I've been told that he's very crafty.
\v 23 \add вүҲFind out all the other\add* placesВҰ137746 whereВҰ137747 he hidesВҰ137748 himselfВҰ137748. Return to me with definite \add information\add*, then I'll goВҰ137755 with you all, andВҰ137743 if he's thereВҰ137749 inВҰ137764 that \add вүҲregion\add*, then I'll searchВҰ137762 for him amongВҰ137764 the \add вүҲpopulation\add* of YehudahВҰ137766.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 \add вүҲSoВҰ137768\add* they \add вүҲleft and returned\add* to ZifВҰ137770 ahead of Sha'ulВҰ137772. \add AtВҰ137777 that time,\add* DavidВҰ137773 and his menВҰ137774 were inВҰ137775 the MaonВҰ137776 wildernessВҰ137775 southВҰ137779 of YeshimonВҰ137780
\v 25 \add вүҲwhen\add* Sha'ul and his menВҰ137784 came to searchВҰ137785 \add for them\add*. \add вүҲWhenВҰ137782\add* DavidВҰ137787 was told, he went \add further south\add* to a \add вүҲrocky hill therein that\add* wilderness, \add вүҲbutВҰ137782\add* Sha'ul \add also\add* heard \add that\add* and followed \add вүҲthem\add*.
\v 26 \add At one point,\add* Sha'ul was on one side of a hillВҰ137805, and David and his men were on the otherВҰ137811 side. David was hurryingВҰ137814 to get away from Sha'ul, butВҰ137802 Sha'ul and his men were trying to surroundВҰ137820 David and his men to captureВҰ137827 them.
\v 27 \add Just\add* thenВҰ137829, a messengerВҰ137829 \add вүҲarrived for\add* Sha'ulВҰ137833, saying, вҖң\add вүҲCome quickly\add* because the PhilistinesВҰ137840 have raided \add вүҲour region\add*.вҖқ
\v 28 \add вүҲSoВҰ137845\add* Sha'ulВҰ137846 \add вүҲhad to give up\add* chasingВҰ137847 DavidВҰ137849 andВҰ137845 wentВҰ137850 to \add вүҲrepel\add* the PhilistinesВҰ137852.
\v 29 David \add also\add* \add вүҲleft that area\add* and stayed in the strongholds \add вүҲaround\add* Eyn-Gedi.
\c 24
\s1 David refuses to kill Sha'ul
\rem /s1 David Spares Saul's Life
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲAfter\add* Sha'ul returned from \add вүҲrepelling\add* the Philistines, they told him that DavidВҰ137864 was \add now\add* inВҰ137867 the Eyn-Gedi wilderness.
\v 2 \add вүҲSo\add* Sha'ulВҰ137876 \add вүҲchose\add* three thousand \add вүҲIsraeli warriors\add* and went \add вүҲsearching\add* for DavidВҰ137883 and his men atВҰ137884 Wild Goats Rocks.
\v 3 OnВҰ137898 the way, as \add #they\add* reached the sheep yards, Sha'ulВҰ137891 \add вүҲwentВҰ137899 into a cave to relieve himself, butВҰ137890\add* DavidВҰ137903 and his menВҰ137904 were \add вүҲhiding there further inside\add* the cave.\x + \xo 24:3: \xt Psa 57 header; Psa 142 header.\x*
\v 4 David'sВҰ137928 menВҰ137929 \add вүҲwhispered\add* to him, вҖңWow, today what Yahweh told you \add вүҲis coming true\add* \add when he said\add*, вҖҳListen, I'm about to give \add вүҲvictory over your enemy\add*, and you will do to him \add вүҲwhatever you think is right\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ Then David \add вүҲsneaked up\add* and \add вүҲquietly\add* cut \add a piece\add* off the edge of Sha'ul's robe.
\v 5 \add вүҲAfterwards\add* \add however,\add* DavidВҰ137937 \add вүҲfelt bad because\add* he'd cut \add a piece\add* off Sha'ul's \add вүҲclothes\add*
\v 6 and he said to his men, вҖң\add вүҲBy Yahweh, I shouldn't have done thatВҰ137988\add* to my masterвҖ”to Yahweh's anointed \add king\add*вҖ”to \add вүҲdo him harm\add* because he's the \add one\add* Yahweh anointed.вҖқ\x + \xo 24:6: \xt 1Sam 26:11.\x*
\v 7 \add *He\add* restrained his menВҰ137994 with \add a few quiet\add* words and \add вүҲwouldn't allow them to attack\add* Sha'ul.
\p Then Sha'ul left the cave and \add вүҲheaded down the path\add*.
\v 8 After \add вүҲwaiting a few moment\add*, David wentВҰ138033 out of the cave and called out behind Sha'ul, вҖңMy master the king.вҖқ \add вүҲWhen\add* Sha'ul turned and looked behind him, David bowed
\v 9 and said, вҖңWhy do you listen to \add вүҲpeople when they sayВҰ138052 that I'm wanting to harm you\add*?
\v 10 Look, \add вүҲyou can see for yourself\add* that Yahweh gave \add вүҲme the opportunity to harm\add* you today in the cave, and some \add of my men\add* wanted me to kill you, butВҰ138066 I \add вүҲshowed you\add* compassion and \add вүҲtold them that\add* I wouldn't \add вүҲdo harm to\add* my master, because he's Yahweh's \add вүҲchosen king\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲYour majesty, look of this piece of your robe that I'm holding\add*, because when I cut it off, I didn'tВҰ138102 kill you. \add вүҲSo now you can see for yourself that I have no evil plans, and I haven't do you any wrong, even though\add* you're \add вүҲambushing me so you can kill me\add*.
\v 12 May Yahweh judge between you and me \add вүҲbecause I'll let Yahweh repay you for any harm against meвҖ”it won'tВҰ138129 be me who works\add* against you.
\v 13 As the ancient proverb says, вҖҳEvil things are done by evil people.вҖҷ \add вүҲButВҰ138153 itВҰ138159 won'tВҰ138158 be me who harms\add* you.
\v 14 Who has Yisrael's king come \add вүҲto find\add*? Who are you chasing after? A dead dog? A flea?\x + \xo 24:14: \xt 1Sam 26:20.\x*
\v 15 May Yahweh \add вүҲtake his judgement seat\add* and judge between me and you, and may he see my case and \add вүҲfind me innocent and save me from you\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲWhen David finished saying that to Sha'ul, Sha'ul called back\add*, вҖңIs that your voice, my son David?вҖқ Then \add *he\add* \add вүҲcried loudly\add*
\v 17 and told DavidВҰ138214, вҖңYou're more righteous than I \add am\add*, because you \add вүҲwere\add* good to me \add вүҲeven when I\add* did evil \add things\add* to you.
\v 18 You've \add вүҲstated\add* that you'veВҰ138244 \add вүҲtreated me well\add*вҖ”how Yahweh \add вүҲgave you the advantage over me, yet\add* you didn't kill me.
\v 19 \add вүҲNow\add* if a man finds his enemy \add unprepared\add*, does he \add just\add* \add вүҲsend him off happily\add*? \add вүҲWell,\add* may YahwehВҰ138264 reward you for \add вүҲyour mercy towards\add* me today.
\v 20 Now listen, I know for certain that you're going to \add вүҲbecome king\add* and that the kingdom of Yisrael will \add вүҲprosper under your leadership\add*.
\v 21 Now \add вүҲpromise\add* me by Yahweh that youВҰ138296 won't \add вүҲdestroy my name from my family line by killing my descendants\add*.вҖқ
\v 22 David promised \add <that\add* to Sha'ul, then Sha'ul \add вүҲwent back home\add* and David and his men returned to \add &their\add* stronghold.
\c 25
\s1 David, Nabal, and Abigil
\rem /s1 Death of Samuel; The Death of Samuel; David, Nabal and Abigail
\s4 Full kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add Later onВҰ138350,\add* Shemuel diedВҰ138340 and all \add вүҲthe IsraelisВҰ138343\add* gatheredВҰ138342 and mournedВҰ138346 for him, then they buriedВҰ138349 him atВҰ138350 his houseВҰ138350 inВҰ138350 RamahВҰ138351.
\rem /s1 Nabal Angers David; David and Abigail; David and the Wife of Nabal
\p Then DavidВҰ138353 left and went to the ParanВҰ138358 wildernessВҰ138357.
\v 2 \add вүҲNow\add* there was a man in MaonВҰ138362 whoseВҰ138363 businessВҰ138363 was in Carmel. \add вүҲHe owned\add* threeВҰ138370 thousand sheep and one thousand goatsВҰ138374, and was \add busy\add* shearingВҰ138376 his sheep atВҰ138362 Carmel.
\v 3 The man's name was NabalВҰ138384, and his wife was AbigailВҰ138387. The wife was \add вүҲwise and very good-looking, whereas\add* the man (who was a Calebite) was harsh and cruel.
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲWhileВҰ138409\add* DavidВҰ138403 was inВҰ138404 the wildernessВҰ138404, he heard that NabalВҰ138408 was shearingВҰ138407 his sheepВҰ138411,
\v 5 \add вүҲso he told\add* ten youngВҰ138416 men, вҖңGo to NabalВҰ138425 atВҰ138429 CarmelВҰ138421 andВҰ138413 \add вүҲgreetВҰ138426\add* him inВҰ138429 my name.
\v 6 ThenВҰ138432 tell him, вҖҳ\add вүҲMake you live long\add*. Peace to you and yourВҰ138437 \add вүҲhouseholdВҰ138437\add* and \add вүҲeverything that belongs to\add* you.
\v 7 Now I'veВҰ138446 heardВҰ138446 those shearersВҰ138448 \add вүҲare working for\add* you, andВҰ138459 your shepherdsВҰ138451 have been \add вүҲliving\add* withВҰ138468 us. We haven't harmed them or \add вүҲtaken anythingВҰ138463 of theirsВҰ138467\add* while they've been inВҰ138468 CarmelВҰ138468.
\v 8 Ask your \add вүҲservants\add* and they'll \add вүҲconfirm this\add*. May \add these\add* youngВҰ138477 menВҰ138477 \add вүҲenjoy your\add* favourВҰ138478 because \add harvesting the wool\add* is a \add вүҲprosperous time\add*, so I request a gift for your servants and for your вҖҳsonвҖҷ, DavidВҰ138496.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ138498\add* David'sВҰ138500 menВҰ138499 wentВҰ138498 and \add вүҲpassed all that onto\add* NabalВҰ138504, and thenВҰ138498 \add вүҲwaitedВҰ138511 for his response\add*.
\v 10 \add вүҲButВҰ138513\add* NabalВҰ138514 answeredВҰ138513 \add *them\add*, вҖң\add вүҲWhy should I care about\add* DavidВҰ138518? Yishay'sВҰ138525 son \add вүҲisn't anyoneВҰ138530 important\add*. There's lot of servants \add вүҲthese days\add* who are \add вүҲon the run from theirВҰ138532\add* \add #masters\add*.
\v 11 This breadВҰ138537 and waterВҰ138540, and the meat thatВҰ138543 I'veВҰ138544 \add вүҲbutchered\add*, is for my shearersВҰ138545. Why should I giveВҰ138546 it to menВҰ138547 when I don'tВҰ138549 even knowВҰ138550 whereВҰ138551 they're from?вҖқ
\p
\v 12 David'sВҰ138558 menВҰ138556 \add вүҲleft\add* andВҰ138555 returnedВҰ138560 \add вүҲto inform him what\add* \add Nabal\add* \add вүҲhad been said\add*.
\v 13 ThenВҰ138568 David told his men, вҖңStrap on \add вүҲyour swords\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ138568 David took\add* around four hundred men, \add вүҲleaving\add* around two hundred with \add &their\add* gear.
\p
\v 14 \add Meanwhile\add*, Nabal'sВҰ138604 wifeВҰ138603 Abigail had been informed by a \add вүҲservant\add*, вҖңListen, DavidВҰ138613 sentВҰ138612 messengersВҰ138614 from the wildernessВҰ138616 to greetВҰ138617 our masterВҰ138620, \add вүҲbutВҰ138602\add* he yelled atВҰ138622 them.
\v 15 \add &Their\add* menВҰ138624 had been very goodВҰ138625 to usвҖ”we were never harmed or \add вүҲhad anythingВҰ138633 go missing\add* when we were inВҰ138639 the countrysideВҰ138640.
\v 16 They \add вүҲprotected\add* us both dayВҰ138650 and nightВҰ138647 \add вүҲfor the whole timeВҰ138653 that weВҰ138654 were\add* tending the sheepВҰ138657.
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ138659\add* now \add вүҲyou should think about it and decide what you can do\add*, because \add no doubt\add* \add вүҲdisaster is about to hit\add* our masterВҰ138671 and all his householdВҰ138675. He's a \add вүҲterrible man who listens to no one\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 \add вүҲSoВҰ138683\add* AbigailВҰ138684 quickly \add collected\add* two hundred loaves of breadВҰ138688, two skins of wine, five butchered sheepВҰ138694, a large basket of roastedВҰ138700 grainВҰ138700, a hundred bunchesВҰ138702 of raisinsВҰ138702, andВҰ138683 two hundred cakesВҰ138704 of figs. She loadedВҰ138705 \add it all\add* on donkeysВҰ138708
\v 19 andВҰ138710 told her \add вүҲservantsВҰ138711\add*, вҖң\add вүҲGo ahead\add* \add with the donkeys\add*. I'll come \add along\add* behind you all.вҖқ \add вүҲButВҰ138710 sheВҰ138720 didn'tВҰ138719 say a word to\add* her husbandВҰ138717 NabalВҰ138718.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲAsВҰ138738 she rode down a hillВҰ138731 and into the ravineВҰ138730, suddenly\add* she encountered DavidВҰ138733 and his menВҰ138734 coming down to meet her.
\v 21 DavidВҰ138740 had told \add <them\add*, вҖң\add WellВҰ138744\add* \add вүҲit was certainly a waste of time looking after that fellow inВҰ138751 the wildernessВҰ138751\add*, andВҰ138740 \add вүҲtaking such care not to take anythingВҰ138760 of his\add*. ThenВҰ138740 \add вүҲall he did was to returnВҰ138761 insults for our goodВҰ138766 behaviour\add*.
\v 22 May GodВҰ138771 \add preserve\add* \add *my\add* enemiesВҰ138772, if I \add вүҲdon't eliminate\add* all of the \add вүҲolder andВҰ138774 young men inВҰ138788 his household before\add* the morningВҰ138786.
\rem /s1 Abigail Intercedes for Nabal
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲWhenВҰ138790\add* AbigailВҰ138791 sawВҰ138790 David, she \add вүҲquickly dismounted\add* from the donkeyВҰ138798 and fell \add вүҲto her knees in frontВҰ138800\add* of David and bowedВҰ138805 \add her faceВҰ138804\add* to the groundВҰ138806.
\v 24 She \add вүҲclutched\add* his feetВҰ138811 andВҰ138808 said, вҖңMy masterВҰ138816, \add вүҲlet the guiltВҰ138817 be\add* onВҰ138813 me myself. Please let your female servant \add вүҲexplain to you\add*вҖ”\add вүЎplease\add* \add вүҲlistenВҰ138823 to what\add* your female servant \add вүҲhas to say\add*.
\v 25 My master, pleaseВҰ138830 \add вүҲdon'tВҰ138856 remain angry at that worthlessВҰ138840\add* man, NabalВҰ138844. His name \add вүҲmeans вҖҳfoolвҖҷ\add* and so he is. \add вүҲHe's a senseless man, butВҰ138852\add* my master, your female servantВҰ138855 didn'tВҰ138856 see the youngВҰ138860 men you sent.
\v 26 And now, my master, as Yahweh lives and as your spirit lives, it's Yahweh who's \add вүҲprevented you from spilling bloodВҰ138877 and taking his punishment into your own hands\add*. And now may your enemiesВҰ138884 and \add вүҲanyone who makes plans\add* againstВҰ138886 my master be like NabalВҰ138883.
