\p
\v 32 вҖңMay Yisrael'sВҰ139006 godВҰ139005 YahwehВҰ139004 be blessedВҰ139003,вҖқ DavidВҰ139001 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ139000\add*. вҖң\add The one\add* who sentВҰ139008 youВҰ139008 to meet me today.
\v 33 And blessed be yourВҰ139014 discernmentВҰ139014 and blessed be you \add yourself\add*, \add вүҲbecause you'veВҰ139018 prevented me from shedding bloodВҰ139022 today\add* and from \add вүҲtaking my own revenge\add*.
\v 34 \add Yes\add* indeed, as YahwehВҰ139030 lives, Yisrael'sВҰ139032 godВҰ139031 \add вүҲprevented me from harmingВҰ139035\add* you. If you hadn't hurried here to meet me, certainly \add вүҲneither NabalВҰ139048 nor any of his older or young men would have survived\add* \add to see\add* the morningВҰ139052 lightВҰ139051.
\v 35 ThenВҰ139056 DavidВҰ139057 \add вүҲaccepted the gifts thatВҰ139060\add* she had broughtВҰ139062 for him, and said, вҖңGo \add вүҲback\add* to your houseВҰ139068 inВҰ139071 peaceВҰ139067. See, I'veВҰ139070 listenedВҰ139070 to \add вүҲwhat you said and grantedВҰ139072 your requestВҰ139073\add*.вҖқ
