\v 36 \add вүҲWhenВҰ139075\add* AbigailВҰ139076 \add вүҲgot home\add* to NabalВҰ139080, wow, \add вүҲhe had put onВҰ139085 a celebration\add* at his houseВҰ139085 \add вүҲwithВҰ139085 a feast fit for\add* a kingВҰ139087. \add вүҲHeВҰ139089 was feeling very contented andВҰ139075 was quite\add* drunkВҰ139093, \add вүҲso\add* she didn'tВҰ139097 tell him \add вүҲanythingВҰ139101 at all\add* untilВҰ139104 it was lightВҰ139106 inВҰ139085 the morningВҰ139107.
\v 37 And so it was inВҰ139110 the morningВҰ139110, when Nabal'sВҰ139113 wine \add вүҲhad worn off\add*, his wife told him \add вүҲwhat she'd done\add*. \add In his rage,\add* \add вүҲhe had a stroke andВҰ139109 becameВҰ139126 totally paralysed\add*
\v 38 for aboutВҰ139130 thenВҰ139129 daysВҰ139131. ThenВҰ139129 YahwehВҰ139133 struckВҰ139132 NabalВҰ139136 andВҰ139129 he diedВҰ139137.
