\v 39 \add вүҲWhenВҰ139139\add* DavidВҰ139140 heard that Nabal had diedВҰ139142, he saidВҰ139144, вҖңBlessed be Yahweh, who has \add вүҲjudged\add* the case of \add вүҲNabal'sВҰ139143 insult\add* andВҰ139139 has \add вүҲprevented\add* his servantВҰ139157 from \add вүҲdoing the wrong thing\add*. And Yahweh has \add вүҲrepaid Nabal for his own evil\add*.вҖқ
