\v 3 \add *They\add* camped atВҰ139294 HakilahВҰ139295 hill (\add вүҲopposite\add* YeshimonВҰ139300) by the pathВҰ139303, \add вүҲbutВҰ139292\add* DavidВҰ139304 stayed inВҰ139294 the wilderness \add вүҲwhen\add* he saw the Sha'ulВҰ139293 was \add вүҲthere trying to get\add* him.
\v 4 (\add *He'd\add* sentВҰ139314 some spiesВҰ139316 andВҰ139317 knewВҰ139317 that Sha'ulВҰ139321 had definitely \add вүҲarrived\add*.)
\v 5 \add That night,\add* DavidВҰ139327 \add вүҲmoved out\add* andВҰ139326 \add вүҲgot\add* to the place where Sha'ul had camped. \add *He\add* \add вүҲcould see where Sha'ul was sleeping\add*, along with Ner'sВҰ139350 son AbnerВҰ139347, his army commanderВҰ139351. Sha'ul was \add вүҲasleep inВҰ139356 the secure centre\add* with his \add вүҲwarriors\add* all aroundВҰ139359 him.
\p
\v 6 DavidВҰ139363 spoke to Ahimelek (the HittiteВҰ139369) andВҰ139362 to AbishaiВҰ139372 (son of Yoab'sВҰ139377 brotherВҰ139376 TseruiahВҰ139375) \add вүҲasking\add*, вҖңWho'll go into the campВҰ139388 with me to Sha'ulВҰ139385?вҖқ
\p Abishai \add вүҲansweredВҰ139362\add*, вҖңI will. I'llВҰ139392 go with you.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ139395 that nightВҰ139402\add* DavidВҰ139396 and AbishaiВҰ139397 \add вүҲcrept into the campВҰ139407\add*. Sha'ulВҰ139404 was asleep \add вүҲthere in the centre\add* withВҰ139407 his spearВҰ139408 stuck into the ground near his headВҰ139412, and AbnerВҰ139414 and \add вүҲothers\add* were lying \add in a circle\add* aroundВҰ139417 himВҰ139417.
