\v 17 ThenВҰ139644 Sha'ulВҰ139645 recognisedВҰ139644 David'sВҰ139649 voice andВҰ139644 \add вүҲcalled back\add*, вҖңIs that your voice, my son David?вҖқ
\p вҖң\add Yes,\add* it is my voice, my masterВҰ139658 the kingВҰ139659.вҖқ DavidВҰ139649 \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\v 18 ThenВҰ139661 he asked, вҖңWhy is my masterВҰ139664 chasingВҰ139665 his servantВҰ139667? What have I done? \add вүҲWhat wrong am I guilty of\add*?
\v 19 Now pleaseВҰ139679 listenВҰ139677, my masterВҰ139680 the kingВҰ139681, to your servant'sВҰ139684 wordsВҰ139683. If it's Yahweh who's incitedВҰ139688 you againstВҰ139689 me, may he \add вүҲaccept\add* an offeringВҰ139691, but if it's \add вүҲpeople\add*, may they be cursedВҰ139696 \add вүҲin frontВҰ139698\add* of Yahweh because they've drivenВҰ139702 me away from \add вүҲenjoying Yahweh's inheritanceВҰ139705 for me\add*,\f + \fr 26:19 \ft This is possibly referring to David not being able to enjoy his piece of land, but we haven't said that in the translation because it's not certain. (It could be referring to having a peaceful or prosperous life, for example.)\f* saying, вҖҳGo \add away andВҰ139676\add* serveВҰ139709 otherВҰ139711 godsВҰ139710.вҖҷ
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ139713\add* now, don'tВҰ139714 let \add вүҲme die far\add* from Yahweh's \add вүҲpresenceВҰ139720\add*. \add It seems that\add* Yisrael'sВҰ139726 kingВҰ139725 has comeВҰ139724 \add all this way\add* to chase a flea, just like someoneВҰ139733 chases a \add вүҲwild bird\add* inВҰ139735 the hills.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 Sha'ulВҰ139738 \add вүҲrespondedВҰ139737\add*, вҖң\add Yes,\add* I've sinnedВҰ139739. \add вүҲGo home\add*, my son DavidВҰ139743. I won'tВҰ139745 \add вүҲwrong\add* you againВҰ139749, becauseВҰ139750 \add вүҲyou spared my lifeВҰ139753 today\add*. \add вүҲYes\add*, I've acted foolishlyВҰ139758 andВҰ139759 \add вүҲbeen following the wrong path\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 вҖңLook, \add вүҲhere's your\add* spear.вҖқ DavidВҰ139764 \add вүҲcalled back\add*. вҖңGet one of \add &your\add* youngВҰ139772 menВҰ139772 \add вүҲto comeВҰ139770 across\add* andВҰ139763 get it.
\v 23 May Yahweh \add вүҲrepay each person for their obedience\add* andВҰ139775 faithfulnessВҰ139783. Yahweh \add вүҲput youВҰ139785 inВҰ139790 a vulnerable position\add* today, butВҰ139775 I wasn't willingВҰ139792 to \add вүҲhurt\add* Yahweh's anointedВҰ139795 \add king\add*.
\v 24 Just as \add вүҲI honoured\add* your life today, so \add to\add* may YahwehВҰ139809 \add вүҲhonour\add* my life andВҰ139798 rescueВҰ139810 me from all \add вүҲmy difficulties\add*.
\p
\v 25 вҖңMay you be blessedВҰ139821, my son David,вҖқ Sha'ul told David. вҖңYou certainly \add вүҲhave both ability and the skill to use it\add*.вҖқ
\p Then DavidВҰ139820 went on his wayВҰ139833 and Sha'ul \add вүҲwent back home\add*.
\c 27
