\p DavidВҰ140041 would tell \add <him\add*, вҖңIn southern YehudahВҰ140045,вҖқ or вҖңSouth of the YerahmeelitesВҰ140049,вҖқ or вҖңIn the southern Kenite \add region\add*вҖқ.
\v 11 DavidВҰ140060 never allowed any man or womanВҰ140056 to live to be able to go back to GatВҰ140062 andВҰ140055 report onВҰ140080 what he'd \add really\add* been doing. \add вүҲThat was how he handled things for the entireВҰ140075 timeВҰ140077\add* thatВҰ140078 he lived inВҰ140080 the Philistine countrysideВҰ140080.
\v 12 \add вүҲButВҰ140083\add* \add King\add* Akish was trustingВҰ140083 DavidВҰ140085, \add вүҲthinking\add*, вҖңHe'll definitely \add вүҲbe hated\add* \add now by\add* his peopleВҰ140089 inВҰ140085 YisraelВҰ140090, \add вүҲso\add* he'll \add вүҲbe forced to remain here as my\add* servantВҰ140093.вҖқ
