\v 3 ThenВҰ141545 the battleВҰ141546 \add вүҲwas fierce\add* around Sha'ulВҰ141549, thenВҰ141545 the \add вүҲPhilistine archers sighted\add* him andВҰ141545 he writhed inВҰ141553 terrible pain \add вүҲfrom the arrows\add*.
\v 4 \add *He\add* said to the \add вүҲman\add* carrying his equipment, вҖңDraw out your sword and pierce me through withВҰ141566 it, lest theseВҰ141571 uncircumcisedВҰ141570 \add вүҲPhilistines\add* come and pierce me through thenВҰ141558 \add вүҲtorture me as I'm dying\add*.вҖқ ButВҰ141558 the \add вүҲman\add* who carried his equipment was very scared and \add вүҲwouldn't do it, so\add* Sha'ulВҰ141559 took \add &his\add* sword and fell onВҰ141566 it.
\v 5 \add вүҲWhenВҰ141597\add* the \add вүҲman\add* carrying his equipment saw that \add *the king\add* was dead, he too fell on his swordВҰ141604 andВҰ141591 died with him.
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ141608\add* Sha'ulВҰ141609, threeВҰ141610 of his sonsВҰ141611, andВҰ141608 the \add вүҲman\add* carrying his equipment all diedВҰ141608 on that same dayВҰ141618, along with all his \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ141617\add*.
